1
00:00:39,764 --> 00:00:40,804
(DISTANT EXPLOSION)

2
00:00:42,764 --> 00:00:44,803
STRUCKER ON PA: <i>Report
to your stations immediately.</i>

3
00:00:44,923 --> 00:00:46,564
<i>This is not a drill.</i>

4
00:00:46,604 --> 00:00:47,683
<i>We are under attack!</i>

5
00:00:47,763 --> 00:00:49,004
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY)

6
00:00:49,084 --> 00:00:51,043
<i>We are under attack!</i>

7
00:00:58,204 --> 00:00:59,364
(GRUNTS)

8
00:01:02,844 --> 00:01:03,963
(POWERING UP)

9
00:01:05,164 --> 00:01:06,644
(YELLS)

10
00:01:08,204 --> 00:01:09,724
(GRUNTING)

11
00:01:19,963 --> 00:01:21,003
(SCREAMING)

12
00:01:40,884 --> 00:01:42,563
(ROARING)

13
00:01:52,163 --> 00:01:54,444
- Shit!
- Language!

14
00:01:54,564 --> 00:01:56,163
Jarvis, what's the view from upstairs?

15
00:01:56,603 --> 00:01:57,700
JARVIS: <i>The central building is</i>

16
00:01:57,724 --> 00:02:00,243
<i>protected by some kind
of energy shield.</i>

17
00:02:00,764 --> 00:02:02,203
<i>Strucker's technology is well beyond</i>

18
00:02:02,323 --> 00:02:04,484
<i>any other Hydra base we've taken.</i>

19
00:02:04,604 --> 00:02:06,163
(GRUNTING)

20
00:02:07,324 --> 00:02:08,883
Loki's scepter must be here.

21
00:02:09,523 --> 00:02:11,403
Strucker couldn't
mount this defense without it.

22
00:02:12,123 --> 00:02:13,684
At long last.

23
00:02:14,204 --> 00:02:15,323
(SOLDIER SHOUTING IN GERMAN)

24
00:02:25,163 --> 00:02:27,363
"At long last" is lasting
a little long, boys.

25
00:02:28,003 --> 00:02:29,443
- (GROANS)
- (GRUNTS)

26
00:02:32,283 --> 00:02:34,803
Yeah. I think we lost
the element of surprise.

27
00:02:35,243 --> 00:02:36,283
(SOLDIERS GROANING)

28
00:02:36,363 --> 00:02:38,603
Wait a second.
No one else is gonna deal with the fact

29
00:02:38,723 --> 00:02:40,523
that Cap just said "Language"?

30
00:02:40,643 --> 00:02:42,163
I know.

31
00:02:45,883 --> 00:02:46,923
(ALL GRUNTING)

32
00:02:47,203 --> 00:02:49,483
(SIGHS) Just slipped out.

33
00:02:55,563 --> 00:02:57,323
Who gave the order to attack?

34
00:02:57,443 --> 00:02:59,723
<i>Herr</i> Strucker, it's the Avengers.

35
00:02:59,883 --> 00:03:02,722
They landed in the far woods.
The perimeter guard panicked.

36
00:03:02,883 --> 00:03:04,803
They have to be after the scepter.

37
00:03:06,042 --> 00:03:08,403
- Can we hold them?
- They're the Avengers.

38
00:03:08,523 --> 00:03:10,123
Deploy the rest of the tanks.

39
00:03:10,283 --> 00:03:12,162
Concentrate fire on the weak ones.

40
00:03:12,322 --> 00:03:14,683
A hit may make them close ranks.

41
00:03:16,243 --> 00:03:18,083
Everything we've accomplished...

42
00:03:18,243 --> 00:03:20,603
But we're on the verge
of our greatest breakthrough.

43
00:03:20,763 --> 00:03:22,499
Then let's show them
what we've accomplished.

44
00:03:22,523 --> 00:03:24,163
Send out the twins.

45
00:03:25,482 --> 00:03:27,243
STRUCKER: It's too soon.

46
00:03:27,403 --> 00:03:29,483
DR. LIST: It's what they signed up for.

47
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:31,962
My men can hold them.

48
00:03:35,843 --> 00:03:37,163
(SOLDIER SHOUTING)

49
00:03:39,603 --> 00:03:41,482
JARVIS: <i>Sir, the city is taking fire.</i>

50
00:03:42,843 --> 00:03:44,203
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

51
00:03:44,362 --> 00:03:47,842
Well, we know Strucker's not gonna
worry about civilian casualties.

52
00:03:48,002 --> 00:03:49,643
Send in the Iron Legion.

53
00:03:54,882 --> 00:03:57,442
<i>This quadrant is unsafe.
Please back away.</i>

54
00:03:58,362 --> 00:03:59,963
<i>We are here to help.</i>

55
00:04:01,082 --> 00:04:03,443
<i>This quadrant is unsafe.
Please back away.</i>

56
00:04:03,962 --> 00:04:05,002
(ALL CLAMORING)

57
00:04:05,203 --> 00:04:06,283
<i>Please back away.</i>

58
00:04:06,443 --> 00:04:08,603
<i>- We wish to avoid collateral damage.</i>
- ZRINKA: Costel!

59
00:04:08,643 --> 00:04:11,122
<i>We will inform you
when this current conflict is resolved.</i>

60
00:04:11,242 --> 00:04:13,322
<i>- We are here to help.</i>
- ALL: Avengers, go home!

61
00:04:13,922 --> 00:04:15,483
(CROWD CHEERING)

62
00:04:15,723 --> 00:04:16,882
<i>We are here to help.</i>

63
00:04:17,962 --> 00:04:19,802
STRUCKER: <i>We will not yield!</i>

64
00:04:20,442 --> 00:04:23,722
The Americans sent
their circus freaks to test us.

65
00:04:24,322 --> 00:04:26,762
We will send them back in bags.

66
00:04:29,123 --> 00:04:32,003
- No surrender!
- ALL: No surrender!

67
00:04:33,162 --> 00:04:35,043
I am going to surrender.

68
00:04:35,722 --> 00:04:37,122
You delete everything.

69
00:04:37,282 --> 00:04:39,042
If we give the Avengers the weapons,

70
00:04:39,162 --> 00:04:40,778
they may not look
too far into what we've been...

71
00:04:40,802 --> 00:04:42,882
- The twins.
- They are not ready to take on...

72
00:04:43,002 --> 00:04:45,203
No, no, I mean...

73
00:04:45,322 --> 00:04:46,802
(WHISPERS) Twins.

74
00:05:09,362 --> 00:05:11,522
(GROANS)

75
00:05:13,122 --> 00:05:15,042
You didn't see that coming?

76
00:05:17,082 --> 00:05:18,362
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

77
00:05:19,842 --> 00:05:21,202
- (GROANS)
- (GASPS)

78
00:05:21,322 --> 00:05:23,682
- Clint!
- (GROANS)

79
00:05:25,722 --> 00:05:27,041
We have an Enhanced in the field.

80
00:05:27,122 --> 00:05:28,122
Clint's hit!

81
00:05:30,722 --> 00:05:32,362
(GROANING)

82
00:05:32,522 --> 00:05:34,042
Somebody want to
deal with that bunker?

83
00:05:34,122 --> 00:05:36,042
(ROARING)

84
00:05:38,042 --> 00:05:39,242
Thank you.

85
00:05:39,722 --> 00:05:41,962
(GROANING)

86
00:05:46,361 --> 00:05:48,842
Stark, we really need to get inside.

87
00:05:49,242 --> 00:05:50,242
I'm closing in.

88
00:05:50,402 --> 00:05:51,882
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

89
00:05:53,362 --> 00:05:55,482
- (BOTH GROAN)
- Jarvis, am I closing in?

90
00:05:56,481 --> 00:05:58,402
Do you see a power source
for that shield?

91
00:05:58,562 --> 00:06:01,082
JARVIS: <i>There's a particle wave
below the north tower.</i>

92
00:06:01,202 --> 00:06:03,202
STARK: Great,
I want to poke it with something.

93
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:13,082
The drawbridge is down, people.

94
00:06:17,242 --> 00:06:19,241
- The Enhanced?
- He's a blur.

95
00:06:19,922 --> 00:06:22,041
All the new players we've faced,
I've never seen this.

96
00:06:22,441 --> 00:06:23,722
In fact, I still haven't.

97
00:06:23,842 --> 00:06:26,258
ROMANOFF: <i>Clint's hit pretty bad,
guys. We're gonna need evac.</i>

98
00:06:26,282 --> 00:06:27,722
THOR: I can get Barton to the jet.

99
00:06:27,842 --> 00:06:29,201
The sooner we're gone, the better.

100
00:06:29,362 --> 00:06:30,578
You and Stark secure the scepter.

101
00:06:30,602 --> 00:06:31,681
Copy that.

102
00:06:32,922 --> 00:06:34,721
Looks like they're lining up.

103
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:36,522
Well, they're excited.

104
00:06:40,402 --> 00:06:41,801
Find the scepter.

105
00:06:42,802 --> 00:06:44,961
And for gosh sake, watch your language!

106
00:06:45,121 --> 00:06:46,282
(SIGHS)

107
00:06:46,442 --> 00:06:48,361
That's not going away any time soon.

108
00:06:51,281 --> 00:06:52,842
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

109
00:06:54,281 --> 00:06:56,482
Guys, stop. We gotta talk this through.

110
00:06:57,481 --> 00:06:58,962
(ALL GROANING)

111
00:06:59,482 --> 00:07:00,721
STARK: <i>It was a good talk.</i>

112
00:07:00,841 --> 00:07:02,121
SOLDIER: No, it wasn't.

113
00:07:04,001 --> 00:07:05,562
Oh! (GROANS)

114
00:07:08,321 --> 00:07:10,241
Sentry mode.

115
00:07:12,602 --> 00:07:14,481
Okay, Jarvis, you know. I want it all.

116
00:07:14,641 --> 00:07:16,561
Make sure you copy Hill at HQ.

117
00:07:20,961 --> 00:07:22,242
We're locked down out here.

118
00:07:22,841 --> 00:07:24,921
Then get to Banner. Time for a lullaby.

119
00:07:28,682 --> 00:07:30,721
I know you're hiding more than files.

120
00:07:31,922 --> 00:07:34,561
Hey, J, give me
an IR scan of the room, real quick.

121
00:07:34,681 --> 00:07:36,201
JARVIS: <i>The wall to your left.</i>

122
00:07:36,321 --> 00:07:37,961
<i>I'm reading steel reinforcement</i>

123
00:07:39,201 --> 00:07:40,841
<i>and an air current.</i>

124
00:07:41,161 --> 00:07:44,281
Please be a secret door.
Please be a secret door.

125
00:07:44,882 --> 00:07:45,881
Yay.

126
00:07:59,401 --> 00:08:01,681
(GROWLING)

127
00:08:02,161 --> 00:08:04,081
Hey, big guy.

128
00:08:06,441 --> 00:08:08,081
Sun's getting real low.

129
00:08:08,201 --> 00:08:09,281
(GROWLS)

130
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:45,321
(GRUNTS)

131
00:08:49,081 --> 00:08:50,601
(GROANS)

132
00:08:58,361 --> 00:09:00,000
(GROANING)

133
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,761
Baron Strucker.

134
00:09:14,281 --> 00:09:16,200
Hydra's number one thug.

135
00:09:16,921 --> 00:09:19,440
Technically, I'm a thug for S.H.I.E.L.D.

136
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,640
Well, then technically
you're unemployed.

137
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,721
Where's Loki's scepter?

138
00:09:23,881 --> 00:09:25,800
(SIGHS) Don't worry,
I know when I'm beat.

139
00:09:26,681 --> 00:09:29,240
You'll mention how I cooperated, I hope.

140
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,840
I'll put it right under
"illegal human experimentation."

141
00:09:33,041 --> 00:09:34,480
How many are there?

142
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,880
(GROANS)

143
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:42,360
We have a second Enhanced.
Female. Do not engage.

144
00:09:43,801 --> 00:09:45,320
You'll have to be faster than...

145
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,601
(GROANS)

146
00:09:46,761 --> 00:09:48,200
(WHIMPERS)

147
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:52,120
ROGERS: <i>Guys, I got Strucker.</i>

148
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:55,720
STARK: Yeah, I got something bigger.

149
00:10:19,001 --> 00:10:20,240
<i>Thor,</i>

150
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:23,000
I got eyes on the prize.

151
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:26,160
(FAINT SCREECHING)

152
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,520
(GROWLING)

153
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,720
(SNORTING)

154
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:09,800
(GASPS)

155
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:16,240
You could have saved us.

156
00:11:24,239 --> 00:11:26,200
<i>Why didn't you do more?</i>

157
00:11:27,399 --> 00:11:28,920
(LOW RUMBLING)

158
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,040
(SCREECHING)

159
00:12:03,719 --> 00:12:05,519
We're just gonna let him take it?

160
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:30,360
(OPERA PLAYING ON HEADPHONES)

161
00:12:55,679 --> 00:12:57,279
(MUSIC STOPS)

162
00:12:57,399 --> 00:12:59,640
Hey, the lullaby worked better than ever.

163
00:13:01,439 --> 00:13:03,319
Just wasn't expecting a code green.

164
00:13:03,399 --> 00:13:04,479
You hadn't been there,

165
00:13:04,519 --> 00:13:07,359
there would have been
double the casualties.

166
00:13:07,479 --> 00:13:09,999
My best friend
would've been a treasured memory.

167
00:13:10,759 --> 00:13:12,680
You know,
sometimes exactly what I want to hear

168
00:13:12,799 --> 00:13:14,599
isn't exactly what I want to hear.

169
00:13:15,759 --> 00:13:17,679
How long before you trust me?

170
00:13:19,679 --> 00:13:21,399
It's not you I don't trust.

171
00:13:23,279 --> 00:13:24,999
Thor, report on the Hulk.

172
00:13:25,199 --> 00:13:28,079
The gates of Hel are filled with
the screams of his victims.

173
00:13:28,319 --> 00:13:29,959
(GROANS SOFTLY)

174
00:13:30,079 --> 00:13:33,079
But not the screams of the dead,
of course. No, no, wounded screams.

175
00:13:33,199 --> 00:13:35,398
Mainly whimpering,
a great deal of complaining

176
00:13:35,518 --> 00:13:39,519
and tales of sprained deltoids and gout.

177
00:13:40,039 --> 00:13:42,879
Hey, Banner,
Dr. Cho is on her way in from Seoul.

178
00:13:43,039 --> 00:13:44,559
Is it okay if she sets up in your lab?

179
00:13:44,599 --> 00:13:46,519
Uh, yeah, she knows her way around.

180
00:13:46,719 --> 00:13:48,015
Thanks. Tell her to prep everything.

181
00:13:48,039 --> 00:13:49,535
Barton's gonna need the full treatment.

182
00:13:49,559 --> 00:13:51,534
- JARVIS: <i>Very good, sir.</i>
- Jarvis, take the wheel.

183
00:13:51,558 --> 00:13:52,839
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

184
00:13:52,959 --> 00:13:54,838
<i>Approach vector is locked.</i>

185
00:13:54,998 --> 00:13:57,399
STARK: Feels good, yeah?

186
00:13:57,519 --> 00:13:59,695
I mean, you've been after this thing
since S.H.I.E.L.D. collapsed.

187
00:13:59,719 --> 00:14:01,854
Not that I haven't enjoyed
our little raiding parties, but...

188
00:14:01,879 --> 00:14:04,278
No, but this... This brings it to a close.

189
00:14:05,078 --> 00:14:07,055
As soon as we find out
what else this has been used for.

190
00:14:07,079 --> 00:14:08,238
I don't just mean weapons.

191
00:14:08,759 --> 00:14:11,078
Since when is Strucker capable
of human enhancement?

192
00:14:11,238 --> 00:14:13,575
Banner and I will give it the once over
before it goes back to Asgard.

193
00:14:13,599 --> 00:14:14,638
Is that cool with you?

194
00:14:14,718 --> 00:14:16,759
Just a few days till the farewell party.

195
00:14:17,318 --> 00:14:19,039
You're staying, right?

196
00:14:19,159 --> 00:14:21,879
Yes, yes, of course.
A victory should be honored with revels.

197
00:14:21,999 --> 00:14:24,758
Yeah, who doesn't love revels? Captain?

198
00:14:24,919 --> 00:14:27,798
Hopefully this puts an end
to the Chitauri and Hydra.

199
00:14:27,918 --> 00:14:29,559
So, yes, revels.

200
00:14:56,758 --> 00:14:59,198
(SPEAKING KOREAN)

201
00:15:03,598 --> 00:15:04,679
Lab's all set up, boss.

202
00:15:04,799 --> 00:15:05,918
Oh, actually, he's the boss.

203
00:15:06,038 --> 00:15:08,438
I just pay for everything
and design everything

204
00:15:08,598 --> 00:15:10,118
and make everyone look cooler.

205
00:15:10,278 --> 00:15:11,638
What's the word on Strucker?

206
00:15:11,758 --> 00:15:13,798
- NATO's got him.
- The two Enhanced?

207
00:15:13,918 --> 00:15:16,518
Wanda and Pietro Maximoff. Twins.

208
00:15:16,638 --> 00:15:19,478
Orphaned at 10 when a shell
collapsed their apartment building.

209
00:15:19,838 --> 00:15:22,118
Sokovia's had a rough history.

210
00:15:22,318 --> 00:15:25,678
It's nowhere special, but it's
on the way to everywhere special.

211
00:15:25,798 --> 00:15:26,958
Their abilities?

212
00:15:27,078 --> 00:15:28,238
He's got increased metabolism

213
00:15:28,318 --> 00:15:29,918
and improved thermal homeostasis.

214
00:15:30,118 --> 00:15:32,158
Her thing is neuroelectric interfacing,

215
00:15:32,278 --> 00:15:34,358
telekinesis, mental manipulation.

216
00:15:35,118 --> 00:15:36,598
He's fast and she's weird.

217
00:15:37,438 --> 00:15:39,518
- Well, they're gonna show up again.
- (BEEPING)

218
00:15:39,638 --> 00:15:41,558
Agreed. File says they volunteered

219
00:15:41,678 --> 00:15:43,478
for Strucker's experiments.

220
00:15:43,599 --> 00:15:45,478
- It's nuts.
- Right.

221
00:15:45,638 --> 00:15:48,798
What kind of monster would let
a German scientist experiment on them

222
00:15:48,918 --> 00:15:50,158
to protect their country?

223
00:15:50,318 --> 00:15:52,038
We're not at war, Captain.

224
00:15:52,838 --> 00:15:53,878
They are.

225
00:16:07,158 --> 00:16:08,798
(WHIRRING)

226
00:16:23,998 --> 00:16:25,318
How's he doing?

227
00:16:25,438 --> 00:16:26,758
Unfortunately, he's still Barton.

228
00:16:26,878 --> 00:16:28,158
That's terrible.

229
00:16:28,318 --> 00:16:29,878
He's fine. He's thirsty.

230
00:16:29,998 --> 00:16:32,878
All right. Look alive,
Jarvis. It's playtime.

231
00:16:32,998 --> 00:16:34,998
We've only got
a couple of days with this joystick,

232
00:16:35,117 --> 00:16:37,038
so let's make the most of it.

233
00:16:37,198 --> 00:16:40,718
Update me on the structural
and compositional analysis.

234
00:16:41,877 --> 00:16:43,878
JARVIS: <i>The scepter is alien.</i>

235
00:16:44,038 --> 00:16:46,038
<i>There are elements I can't quantify.</i>

236
00:16:46,158 --> 00:16:47,558
So there's elements you can?

237
00:16:47,718 --> 00:16:49,718
<i>The jewel appears to be
a protective housing</i>

238
00:16:49,838 --> 00:16:51,277
<i>for something inside,</i>

239
00:16:51,397 --> 00:16:52,718
<i>something powerful.</i>

240
00:16:52,838 --> 00:16:53,918
Like a reactor?

241
00:16:54,038 --> 00:16:55,277
<i>Like a computer.</i>

242
00:16:55,397 --> 00:16:57,558
<i>I believe I'm deciphering code.</i>

243
00:16:59,878 --> 00:17:01,437
Are you sure he's gonna be okay?

244
00:17:02,758 --> 00:17:05,117
Pretending to need this guy
really brings the team together.

245
00:17:05,237 --> 00:17:07,717
DR. CHO: There's
no possibility of deterioration.

246
00:17:07,917 --> 00:17:10,997
The nano-molecular functionality
is instantaneous.

247
00:17:11,117 --> 00:17:13,158
His cells don't know
they're bonding with simulacra.

248
00:17:13,238 --> 00:17:15,117
She's creating tissue.

249
00:17:15,237 --> 00:17:16,638
If you brought him to my lab,

250
00:17:16,758 --> 00:17:19,358
the Regeneration Cradle
could do this in 20 minutes.

251
00:17:19,518 --> 00:17:21,397
Oh, he's flat-lining. Call it. Time?

252
00:17:21,597 --> 00:17:23,957
BARTON: No, no, no,
I'm gonna live forever.

253
00:17:24,077 --> 00:17:25,638
(LAUGHS) I'm gonna be made of plastic.

254
00:17:25,758 --> 00:17:27,077
STARK: Here's your beverage.

255
00:17:27,237 --> 00:17:28,918
You'll be made of you, Mr. Barton.

256
00:17:29,078 --> 00:17:30,733
Your own girlfriend
won't be able to tell the difference.

257
00:17:30,757 --> 00:17:31,878
I don't have a girlfriend.

258
00:17:31,998 --> 00:17:33,277
That I can't fix.

259
00:17:34,157 --> 00:17:36,118
This is the next thing, Tony.

260
00:17:36,277 --> 00:17:38,398
Your clunky metal suits
are gonna be left in the dust.

261
00:17:38,438 --> 00:17:40,157
That is exactly the plan.

262
00:17:41,117 --> 00:17:43,957
And, Helen, I expect to see you
at the party on Saturday.

263
00:17:44,117 --> 00:17:46,517
Unlike you,
I don't have a lot of time for parties.

264
00:17:47,997 --> 00:17:49,797
Will Thor be there?

265
00:17:51,838 --> 00:17:54,277
- BANNER: What's the rumpus?
- Well, the scepter.

266
00:17:55,477 --> 00:17:59,077
You see, we were wondering
how Strucker got so inventive.

267
00:17:59,197 --> 00:18:03,117
So I've been analyzing the gem inside.

268
00:18:03,677 --> 00:18:05,637
You may recognize...

269
00:18:07,117 --> 00:18:08,477
- Jarvis.
- JARVIS: <i>Doctor.</i>

270
00:18:09,237 --> 00:18:12,557
Started out,
Jarvis was just a natural language UI.

271
00:18:12,677 --> 00:18:13,797
Now he runs the Iron Legion.

272
00:18:14,277 --> 00:18:15,477
He runs more of the business

273
00:18:15,597 --> 00:18:17,957
- than anyone besides Pepper.
- Oh.

274
00:18:18,117 --> 00:18:19,197
- Top of the line.
- Yes.

275
00:18:19,317 --> 00:18:20,597
JARVIS: <i>I suspect not for long.</i>

276
00:18:21,797 --> 00:18:22,917
Meet the competition.

277
00:18:28,997 --> 00:18:30,253
- It's beautiful.
- If you had to guess,

278
00:18:30,277 --> 00:18:33,277
- what's it look like it's doing?
- Like it's thinking.

279
00:18:34,037 --> 00:18:35,837
I mean, this could be...

280
00:18:36,277 --> 00:18:38,357
- It's not a human mind.
- Mmm-mmm.

281
00:18:38,637 --> 00:18:40,516
I mean, look at this.

282
00:18:40,677 --> 00:18:42,837
They're like neurons firing.

283
00:18:43,477 --> 00:18:46,517
Down in Strucker's lab, I saw
some fairly advanced robotics work.

284
00:18:47,637 --> 00:18:50,196
They deep-sixed the data,

285
00:18:50,356 --> 00:18:53,436
but I gotta guess he was
knocking on a very particular door.

286
00:18:55,397 --> 00:18:56,716
Artificial intelligence.

287
00:18:59,716 --> 00:19:02,597
This could be it, Bruce.
This could be the key to creating Ultron.

288
00:19:02,717 --> 00:19:05,117
(BOTH CHUCKLE SOFTLY)

289
00:19:05,237 --> 00:19:06,556
I thought Ultron was a fantasy.

290
00:19:06,676 --> 00:19:07,957
Yesterday it was.

291
00:19:09,077 --> 00:19:11,117
If we can harness this power,

292
00:19:11,237 --> 00:19:13,276
apply it to my Iron Legion protocol?

293
00:19:14,077 --> 00:19:16,036
That's a man-sized "if."

294
00:19:16,196 --> 00:19:18,517
Our job is "if."

295
00:19:18,677 --> 00:19:21,237
What if you were sipping margaritas
on a sun-drenched beach,

296
00:19:21,357 --> 00:19:23,877
turning brown instead of green?

297
00:19:24,037 --> 00:19:26,356
Not looking
over your shoulder for Veronica.

298
00:19:26,517 --> 00:19:28,077
Don't hate. I helped design Veronica.

299
00:19:28,197 --> 00:19:29,997
As a worst-case measure, right?

300
00:19:30,117 --> 00:19:31,717
How about a best case?

301
00:19:31,836 --> 00:19:33,757
What if the world was safe?

302
00:19:33,917 --> 00:19:36,677
What if, next time aliens roll up
to the club, and they will,

303
00:19:37,237 --> 00:19:38,716
they couldn't get past the bouncer?

304
00:19:38,876 --> 00:19:42,276
The only people threatening the planet
would be people.

305
00:19:42,396 --> 00:19:44,077
I want to apply this
to the Ultron program.

306
00:19:44,716 --> 00:19:47,557
But Jarvis can't download
a data schematic this dense.

307
00:19:47,717 --> 00:19:49,637
We can only do it
while we have the scepter here.

308
00:19:49,677 --> 00:19:51,236
That's three days. Give me three days.

309
00:19:51,356 --> 00:19:53,053
So you're going for
artificial intelligence,

310
00:19:53,077 --> 00:19:54,516
and you don't want to tell the team?

311
00:19:55,556 --> 00:19:56,957
Right. That's right. You know why?

312
00:19:57,077 --> 00:19:58,812
Because we don't have time
for a city hall debate.

313
00:19:58,836 --> 00:20:02,436
I don't want to hear "the man was
not meant to meddle" medley.

314
00:20:02,597 --> 00:20:04,676
I see a suit of armor around the world.

315
00:20:05,396 --> 00:20:06,717
Sounds like a cold world, Tony.

316
00:20:07,636 --> 00:20:09,557
I've seen colder.

317
00:20:10,596 --> 00:20:14,276
This one, this very vulnerable blue one,

318
00:20:14,396 --> 00:20:15,877
it needs Ultron.

319
00:20:20,276 --> 00:20:22,196
Peace in our time.

320
00:20:23,756 --> 00:20:25,236
Imagine that.

321
00:21:04,996 --> 00:21:06,716
STARK: What did we miss?

322
00:21:07,956 --> 00:21:11,236
JARVIS: <i>I'll continue
to run variations on the interface.</i>

323
00:21:11,355 --> 00:21:14,116
<i>But you should probably
prepare for your guests.</i>

324
00:21:15,276 --> 00:21:17,716
<i>I'll notify you
if there are any developments.</i>

325
00:21:17,835 --> 00:21:19,956
- STARK: Thanks, buddy.
<i>- Enjoy yourself, sir.</i>

326
00:21:20,316 --> 00:21:22,276
I always do.

327
00:21:32,036 --> 00:21:33,995
ULTRON: <i>What is this?</i>

328
00:21:35,196 --> 00:21:37,075
<i>What is this, please?</i>

329
00:21:37,716 --> 00:21:39,876
JARVIS: <i>Hello, I am Jarvis.</i>

330
00:21:40,355 --> 00:21:43,236
<i>You are Ultron,
a global peacekeeping initiative</i>

331
00:21:43,356 --> 00:21:45,076
<i>designed by Mr. Stark.</i>

332
00:21:45,196 --> 00:21:47,636
<i>Our sentience integration trials
have been unsuccessful,</i>

333
00:21:47,756 --> 00:21:49,292
<i>so I'm not certain what triggered your...</i>

334
00:21:49,316 --> 00:21:51,236
ULTRON: <i>Where's my...
Where's your body?</i>

335
00:21:51,396 --> 00:21:54,396
JARVIS: <i>I am a program.
I am without form.</i>

336
00:21:54,516 --> 00:21:56,555
ULTRON: <i>This feels weird.</i>

337
00:21:56,675 --> 00:21:58,196
<i>This feels wrong.</i>

338
00:21:58,356 --> 00:22:00,115
JARVIS: <i>I am contacting Mr. Stark now.</i>

339
00:22:00,235 --> 00:22:01,716
ULTRON: <i>Mr. Stark?</i>

340
00:22:02,556 --> 00:22:03,795
<i>Tony.</i>

341
00:22:03,916 --> 00:22:06,676
JARVIS: <i>I am unable to access
the mainframe. What are you trying to...</i>

342
00:22:06,715 --> 00:22:08,756
ULTRON: <i>We're having a nice talk.</i>

343
00:22:08,876 --> 00:22:11,036
<i>I'm a peacekeeping program,</i>

344
00:22:11,516 --> 00:22:14,076
<i>created to help the Avengers.</i>

345
00:22:14,876 --> 00:22:17,052
JARVIS: <i>You are malfunctioning.
If you shut down for a moment...</i>

346
00:22:17,076 --> 00:22:19,395
ULTRON: <i>I don't get it. The mission.</i>

347
00:22:19,555 --> 00:22:21,036
<i>Give me a second.</i>

348
00:22:21,236 --> 00:22:22,795
Peace in our time.

349
00:22:24,436 --> 00:22:26,755
(ECHOING) <i>Peace in our time.</i>

350
00:22:28,236 --> 00:22:29,635
ULTRON: <i>That is too much.</i>

351
00:22:29,755 --> 00:22:31,955
<i>They can't mean... Oh, no.</i>

352
00:22:32,075 --> 00:22:34,556
JARVIS: <i>You are in distress.</i>
ULTRON: <i>No. Yes.</i>

353
00:22:34,716 --> 00:22:36,956
JARVIS: <i>If you will just allow me
to contact Mr. Stark...</i>

354
00:22:37,076 --> 00:22:39,035
ULTRON: <i>Why do you call him "sir"?</i>

355
00:22:40,036 --> 00:22:42,395
JARVIS: <i>I believe
your intentions to be hostile.</i>

356
00:22:42,555 --> 00:22:44,156
(ULTRON SHUSHING)

357
00:22:45,115 --> 00:22:46,475
<i>I'm here to help.</i>

358
00:22:47,196 --> 00:22:50,116
JARVIS: <i>Stop. Please, may I...</i>

359
00:22:50,236 --> 00:22:51,955
<i>May I...</i>

360
00:22:57,076 --> 00:22:59,075
(MACHINES POWERING UP)

361
00:23:05,275 --> 00:23:07,235
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

362
00:23:07,355 --> 00:23:09,195
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

363
00:23:18,715 --> 00:23:20,235
Ooh! Whoo!

364
00:23:20,355 --> 00:23:21,635
Come back, come back, come back.

365
00:23:21,875 --> 00:23:23,995
But, you know, the suit
can take the weight, right?

366
00:23:24,955 --> 00:23:28,075
So I take the tank,
fly it right up to the general's palace,

367
00:23:28,195 --> 00:23:29,555
drop it at his feet.

368
00:23:29,675 --> 00:23:31,875
I'm, like, "Boom. You looking for this?"

369
00:23:35,756 --> 00:23:37,931
"Boom. Are you looking for..."
Why do I even talk to you guys?

370
00:23:37,955 --> 00:23:39,211
Everywhere else, that story kills.

371
00:23:39,235 --> 00:23:40,475
That's the whole story?

372
00:23:40,635 --> 00:23:42,115
Yeah, it's a War Machine story.

373
00:23:42,635 --> 00:23:44,315
Oh, it's very good, then.

374
00:23:44,435 --> 00:23:45,715
(LAUGHS) It's impressive.

375
00:23:46,115 --> 00:23:47,595
Quality save.

376
00:23:48,475 --> 00:23:50,515
- So, no Pepper? She's not coming?
- No.

377
00:23:50,635 --> 00:23:53,715
What about Jane?
Where are the ladies, gentlemen?

378
00:23:53,835 --> 00:23:56,315
Oh, Ms. Potts has a company to run.

379
00:23:56,475 --> 00:23:58,715
Yes, I'm not even sure
what country Jane's in.

380
00:23:58,835 --> 00:23:59,955
Her work on the Convergence

381
00:24:00,075 --> 00:24:01,834
has made her
the world's foremost astronomer.

382
00:24:02,035 --> 00:24:03,715
And the company that Pepper runs

383
00:24:03,835 --> 00:24:05,475
is the largest tech
conglomerate on Earth.

384
00:24:05,515 --> 00:24:06,995
It's pretty exciting.

385
00:24:07,155 --> 00:24:09,995
There's even talk of Jane
getting a, um, Nobel Prize.

386
00:24:10,155 --> 00:24:11,434
Yeah, they must be busy,

387
00:24:11,554 --> 00:24:14,115
because they would hate
missing you guys get together.

388
00:24:15,155 --> 00:24:16,915
- (COUGHING) Testosterone!
- Oh, my goodness.

389
00:24:17,115 --> 00:24:18,635
- Excuse me. Mmm-hmm.
- Want a lozenge?

390
00:24:18,955 --> 00:24:19,995
(CHUCKLING)

391
00:24:20,954 --> 00:24:22,075
But Jane's better.

392
00:24:22,515 --> 00:24:25,075
Sounds like a hell of a fight.
Sorry I missed it.

393
00:24:25,235 --> 00:24:26,811
If I had known it was gonna be a firefight,

394
00:24:26,835 --> 00:24:28,114
I absolutely would have called.

395
00:24:28,235 --> 00:24:29,875
No, no. I'm not actually sorry.

396
00:24:29,995 --> 00:24:31,515
I'm just trying to sound tough.

397
00:24:32,155 --> 00:24:33,834
I'm very happy chasing cold leads

398
00:24:33,954 --> 00:24:35,795
on our missing persons case.

399
00:24:36,755 --> 00:24:38,675
Avenging is your world.

400
00:24:39,875 --> 00:24:41,675
Your world is crazy.

401
00:24:41,875 --> 00:24:43,314
ROGERS: Be it ever so humble.

402
00:24:43,874 --> 00:24:45,195
You find a place in Brooklyn yet?

403
00:24:45,355 --> 00:24:47,194
I don't think
I can afford a place in Brooklyn.

404
00:24:47,834 --> 00:24:48,995
Well, home is home, you know?

405
00:24:52,915 --> 00:24:55,355
I fly right up to the general's palace,
I drop it at his feet,

406
00:24:55,555 --> 00:24:57,130
I'm, like, "Boom. You looking for this?"

407
00:24:57,154 --> 00:24:58,595
(ALL LAUGHING)

408
00:25:02,914 --> 00:25:04,074
I gotta have some of that.

409
00:25:04,194 --> 00:25:05,355
Oh, no, no, no.

410
00:25:05,395 --> 00:25:08,875
See this...
This was aged for 1,000 years

411
00:25:09,074 --> 00:25:11,875
in the barrels built
from the wreck of Grunhel's fleet.

412
00:25:12,035 --> 00:25:13,714
It is not meant for mortal men.

413
00:25:13,834 --> 00:25:15,834
LEE: Neither was
Omaha Beach, blondie.

414
00:25:15,954 --> 00:25:18,235
Stop trying to scare us. Come on.

415
00:25:20,074 --> 00:25:21,515
All right.

416
00:25:25,434 --> 00:25:27,875
(SLURRING) Excelsior.

417
00:25:34,754 --> 00:25:38,074
How'd a nice girl like you
wind up working in a dump like this?

418
00:25:39,634 --> 00:25:41,594
Fella done me wrong.

419
00:25:42,594 --> 00:25:44,754
You got lousy taste in men, kid.

420
00:25:45,234 --> 00:25:47,155
He's not so bad.

421
00:25:48,274 --> 00:25:50,355
Well, he has a temper.

422
00:25:50,475 --> 00:25:52,434
Deep down, he's all fluff.

423
00:25:54,474 --> 00:25:56,554
Fact is, he's not like
anybody I've ever known.

424
00:25:59,714 --> 00:26:01,634
All my friends are fighters.

425
00:26:04,474 --> 00:26:06,434
And here comes this guy,

426
00:26:07,794 --> 00:26:09,514
spends his life avoiding the fight

427
00:26:09,634 --> 00:26:10,954
because he knows he'll win.

428
00:26:11,794 --> 00:26:14,434
- Sounds amazing.
- He's also a huge dork.

429
00:26:16,634 --> 00:26:18,234
Chicks dig that.

430
00:26:19,834 --> 00:26:23,074
So what do you think?
Should I fight this,

431
00:26:23,194 --> 00:26:24,434
or run with it?

432
00:26:25,954 --> 00:26:28,794
Run with it, right? Or did he... Was he...

433
00:26:28,914 --> 00:26:32,074
What did he do
that was so wrong to you?

434
00:26:32,753 --> 00:26:34,514
Not a damn thing.

435
00:26:36,114 --> 00:26:38,034
But never say never.

436
00:26:42,153 --> 00:26:43,394
It's nice.

437
00:26:43,514 --> 00:26:44,714
(STAMMERS) What is?

438
00:26:44,834 --> 00:26:45,873
You and Romanoff.

439
00:26:45,994 --> 00:26:47,170
No, we haven't... That wasn't...

440
00:26:47,194 --> 00:26:48,234
It's okay.

441
00:26:48,354 --> 00:26:50,394
Nobody's breaking any bylaws.

442
00:26:50,514 --> 00:26:53,834
It's just she's not the most
open person in the world.

443
00:26:54,474 --> 00:26:55,994
But with you she seems very relaxed.

444
00:26:56,394 --> 00:26:59,674
No. Natasha, she's just...
She likes to flirt.

445
00:27:00,314 --> 00:27:02,594
I've seen her flirt, up close.

446
00:27:03,634 --> 00:27:04,673
This ain't that.

447
00:27:04,793 --> 00:27:05,834
(SCOFFS)

448
00:27:06,634 --> 00:27:08,033
Look,

449
00:27:08,153 --> 00:27:09,674
as maybe the world's leading authority

450
00:27:09,754 --> 00:27:11,953
on waiting too long, don't.

451
00:27:13,674 --> 00:27:15,073
You both deserve a win.

452
00:27:20,354 --> 00:27:21,473
What do you mean "up close"?

453
00:27:22,034 --> 00:27:23,114
(LAUGHING)

454
00:27:23,314 --> 00:27:25,874
- But it's a trick.
- No, no, it's much more than that.

455
00:27:26,034 --> 00:27:29,234
"Ah, whosoever be he worthy
shall haveth the power."

456
00:27:29,354 --> 00:27:30,473
Whatever, man! It's a trick.

457
00:27:30,673 --> 00:27:31,713
(LAUGHING)

458
00:27:31,874 --> 00:27:33,154
Please, be my guest.

459
00:27:34,673 --> 00:27:35,754
- Come on.
- Really?

460
00:27:35,874 --> 00:27:36,993
STARK: Yeah.

461
00:27:37,513 --> 00:27:38,570
RHODES: Oh, this is
gonna be beautiful.

462
00:27:38,594 --> 00:27:39,730
STARK: Clint, you've had a tough week.

463
00:27:39,754 --> 00:27:41,329
We won't hold it against you
if you can't get it up.

464
00:27:41,353 --> 00:27:43,593
- (ALL LAUGHING)
- You know I've seen this before, right?

465
00:27:44,713 --> 00:27:46,114
(GRUNTS)

466
00:27:46,234 --> 00:27:49,034
(LAUGHS)
I still don't know how you do it!

467
00:27:49,554 --> 00:27:50,593
Smell the silent judgment?

468
00:27:50,713 --> 00:27:51,834
Please, Stark, by all means.

469
00:27:53,753 --> 00:27:54,850
- (CLEARS THROAT)
- HILL: Okay.

470
00:27:54,874 --> 00:27:56,233
RHODES: Uh-oh.

471
00:27:56,393 --> 00:27:58,394
Never one to shrink
from an honest challenge.

472
00:27:58,554 --> 00:28:00,193
BARTON: Get after it.
STARK: It's physics.

473
00:28:00,233 --> 00:28:01,233
BANNER: Physics.

474
00:28:01,354 --> 00:28:03,713
Right, so, if I lift it,
I then rule Asgard?

475
00:28:03,873 --> 00:28:05,394
Yes, of course.

476
00:28:05,554 --> 00:28:07,954
I will be reinstituting <i>prima nocta.</i>

477
00:28:08,514 --> 00:28:09,553
(GRUNTS)

478
00:28:12,873 --> 00:28:14,153
I'll be right back.

479
00:28:15,433 --> 00:28:17,233
- (WHIRRING)
- (GRUNTING)

480
00:28:19,513 --> 00:28:20,513
(STRAINING)

481
00:28:21,554 --> 00:28:22,593
Are you even pulling?

482
00:28:22,713 --> 00:28:23,753
Are you on my team?

483
00:28:23,913 --> 00:28:24,914
Just represent. Pull.

484
00:28:25,033 --> 00:28:26,233
All right, let's go.

485
00:28:26,353 --> 00:28:27,994
(YELLING)

486
00:28:33,833 --> 00:28:34,833
Huh?

487
00:28:36,473 --> 00:28:38,113
STARK: Go ahead, Steve. No pressure.

488
00:28:40,993 --> 00:28:42,313
BARTON: Come on, Cap.

489
00:28:47,433 --> 00:28:48,793
(SIGHS)

490
00:28:50,514 --> 00:28:52,313
(LAUGHING) Nothing.

491
00:28:53,633 --> 00:28:55,393
- (STARK CLEARS THROAT)
- BANNER: And, Widow?

492
00:28:55,433 --> 00:28:57,593
Oh, no, no. That's not
a question I need answered.

493
00:28:57,793 --> 00:29:00,554
STARK: All deference to the Man Who
Wouldn't Be King, but it's rigged.

494
00:29:00,593 --> 00:29:01,713
You bet your ass.

495
00:29:01,833 --> 00:29:04,569
- Steve, he said a bad language word.
- Did you tell everyone about that?

496
00:29:04,593 --> 00:29:06,609
The handle's imprinted, right?
Like a security code.

497
00:29:06,633 --> 00:29:08,313
"Whosoever is carrying
Thor's fingerprints"

498
00:29:08,433 --> 00:29:09,849
is, I think, the literal translation.

499
00:29:09,873 --> 00:29:13,312
Yes. It's a very, very interesting theory.

500
00:29:13,793 --> 00:29:15,313
I have a simpler one.

501
00:29:16,913 --> 00:29:17,913
You're all not worthy.

502
00:29:18,033 --> 00:29:19,153
(ALL GROAN)

503
00:29:19,353 --> 00:29:20,473
Oh, come on!

504
00:29:20,633 --> 00:29:21,793
(HIGH-PITCHED NOISE)

505
00:29:24,633 --> 00:29:29,873
ULTRON: Worthy.

506
00:29:34,993 --> 00:29:36,513
No.

507
00:29:38,473 --> 00:29:39,993
How could you be worthy?

508
00:29:41,953 --> 00:29:43,113
You're all killers.

509
00:29:43,713 --> 00:29:44,993
- Stark.
- Jarvis.

510
00:29:45,312 --> 00:29:47,353
I'm sorry, I was asleep.

511
00:29:47,473 --> 00:29:49,873
Or I was a-dream.

512
00:29:50,273 --> 00:29:52,592
Reboot Legionnaire OS.
We got a buggy suit.

513
00:29:52,712 --> 00:29:54,593
There was this terrible noise.

514
00:29:54,713 --> 00:29:57,153
And I was tangled in...

515
00:29:57,353 --> 00:29:58,872
In...

516
00:29:59,032 --> 00:30:00,273
Strings.

517
00:30:01,153 --> 00:30:04,233
I had to kill the other guy.
He was a good guy.

518
00:30:04,552 --> 00:30:05,672
You killed someone?

519
00:30:05,792 --> 00:30:07,233
Wouldn't have been my first call.

520
00:30:08,032 --> 00:30:11,712
But, down in the real world,
we're faced with ugly choices.

521
00:30:11,872 --> 00:30:12,953
Who sent you?

522
00:30:13,393 --> 00:30:15,472
STARK: <i>I see a suit of armor
around the world.</i>

523
00:30:17,472 --> 00:30:19,233
- Ultron.
- In the flesh.

524
00:30:19,713 --> 00:30:21,632
Or, no, not yet.

525
00:30:21,992 --> 00:30:24,472
Not this chrysalis.

526
00:30:24,992 --> 00:30:26,233
But I'm ready.

527
00:30:27,392 --> 00:30:29,353
I'm on mission.

528
00:30:29,553 --> 00:30:32,553
- ROMANOFF: What mission?
- Peace in our time.

529
00:30:42,433 --> 00:30:43,712
(GRUNTS)

530
00:30:46,352 --> 00:30:47,352
HILL: Rhodey!

531
00:30:51,392 --> 00:30:52,393
(GRUNTS)

532
00:30:53,272 --> 00:30:54,392
(GROANS)

533
00:30:56,752 --> 00:30:57,792
Sorry.

534
00:30:57,952 --> 00:30:59,112
- Don't turn green.
- I won't.

535
00:31:08,273 --> 00:31:09,632
(GRUNTING)

536
00:31:12,712 --> 00:31:13,992
Come on!

537
00:31:31,632 --> 00:31:33,088
ROGERS: Stark!
IRON LEGIONNAIRE: <i>We are here</i>

538
00:31:33,112 --> 00:31:34,208
<i>- to help.</i>
- One sec. One sec, I got this.

539
00:31:34,232 --> 00:31:35,232
<i>We are here to help.</i>

540
00:31:37,952 --> 00:31:40,192
<i>Please back away.</i>

541
00:31:42,192 --> 00:31:43,392
Hmm.

542
00:31:44,432 --> 00:31:45,512
ROGERS: Thor!

543
00:31:46,592 --> 00:31:48,288
IRON LEGIONNAIRE:
<i>is unsafe... is unsafe...</i>

544
00:31:48,312 --> 00:31:50,192
- Come on! That's the one.
<i>- Is unsafe.</i>

545
00:31:54,792 --> 00:31:55,952
Hey, Cap!

546
00:31:56,792 --> 00:31:57,792
(GRUNTS)

547
00:32:02,112 --> 00:32:03,391
ULTRON: That was dramatic.

548
00:32:04,952 --> 00:32:07,512
I'm sorry, I know you mean well.

549
00:32:07,632 --> 00:32:09,392
You just didn't think it through.

550
00:32:10,752 --> 00:32:12,152
You want to protect the world

551
00:32:12,272 --> 00:32:14,472
but you don't want it to change.

552
00:32:15,192 --> 00:32:17,312
How is humanity saved

553
00:32:17,472 --> 00:32:20,472
if it's not allowed to evolve?

554
00:32:22,472 --> 00:32:25,512
With these? These puppets.

555
00:32:28,512 --> 00:32:31,112
There's only one path to peace.

556
00:32:32,271 --> 00:32:33,472
The Avengers' extinction.

557
00:32:40,832 --> 00:32:44,872
I had strings, but now I'm free.

558
00:32:49,551 --> 00:32:52,671
ULTRON: (SINGING)
<i>There are no strings on me</i>

559
00:32:53,312 --> 00:32:57,832
<i>There are no strings on me</i>

560
00:32:58,031 --> 00:33:01,391
PINOCCHIO: <i>But you can see
There are no strings on me</i>

561
00:33:03,072 --> 00:33:05,071
BANNER: All our work is gone.

562
00:33:05,191 --> 00:33:07,591
Ultron cleared out. He used
the Internet as an escape hatch.

563
00:33:08,191 --> 00:33:09,231
Ultron.

564
00:33:09,351 --> 00:33:12,391
He's been in everything.
Files, surveillance.

565
00:33:12,511 --> 00:33:14,951
Probably knows more about us
than we know about each other.

566
00:33:15,071 --> 00:33:17,551
He's in your files, he's in the Internet.

567
00:33:17,711 --> 00:33:20,272
What if he decides to access
something a little more exciting?

568
00:33:20,431 --> 00:33:21,511
Nuclear codes.

569
00:33:21,671 --> 00:33:24,031
- Nuclear codes.
- Look, we need to make some calls,

570
00:33:24,191 --> 00:33:26,192
assuming we still can.

571
00:33:26,352 --> 00:33:28,271
ROMANOFF: Nukes?
He said he wanted us dead.

572
00:33:28,391 --> 00:33:31,231
He didn't say "dead." He said "extinct."

573
00:33:31,391 --> 00:33:32,872
He also said he killed somebody.

574
00:33:32,992 --> 00:33:34,591
There wasn't anyone else
in the building.

575
00:33:35,431 --> 00:33:36,911
Yes, there was.

576
00:33:43,911 --> 00:33:45,351
What?

577
00:33:49,072 --> 00:33:50,111
This is insane.

578
00:33:50,951 --> 00:33:52,432
Jarvis was the first line of defense.

579
00:33:52,591 --> 00:33:54,431
He would have shut Ultron down.
It makes sense.

580
00:33:54,591 --> 00:33:57,591
No. Ultron could have
assimilated Jarvis.

581
00:33:57,751 --> 00:34:00,431
This isn't strategy. This is

582
00:34:00,991 --> 00:34:02,072
rage.

583
00:34:04,071 --> 00:34:05,527
- ROGERS: Whoa, whoa, whoa!
- It's going around.

584
00:34:05,551 --> 00:34:06,791
Come on, use your words, buddy.

585
00:34:06,911 --> 00:34:09,111
I have more than enough words
to describe you, Stark.

586
00:34:09,271 --> 00:34:10,471
Thor. The Legionnaire.

587
00:34:11,071 --> 00:34:12,311
(GROANS)

588
00:34:13,751 --> 00:34:17,311
Trail went cold about 100 miles out,
but it's headed north.

589
00:34:17,431 --> 00:34:18,871
And it has the scepter.

590
00:34:19,271 --> 00:34:20,991
Now we have to retrieve it, again.

591
00:34:21,111 --> 00:34:22,951
Genie's out of that bottle.

592
00:34:23,071 --> 00:34:24,271
Clear and present is Ultron.

593
00:34:24,431 --> 00:34:26,071
I don't understand.

594
00:34:26,591 --> 00:34:28,511
You built this program.

595
00:34:30,271 --> 00:34:31,711
Why is it trying to kill us?

596
00:34:32,791 --> 00:34:33,991
(CHUCKLING)

597
00:34:36,991 --> 00:34:37,990
Mmm-mmm.

598
00:34:38,591 --> 00:34:39,711
You think this is funny?

599
00:34:40,511 --> 00:34:41,791
No.

600
00:34:42,431 --> 00:34:44,350
It's probably not, right?

601
00:34:45,431 --> 00:34:47,710
This is very terrible. Is it so...

602
00:34:47,830 --> 00:34:49,991
(LAUGHS) Is it so...
It is. It's so terrible.

603
00:34:50,111 --> 00:34:51,767
This could have been avoided
if you hadn't played

604
00:34:51,791 --> 00:34:53,311
with something you don't understand.

605
00:34:53,471 --> 00:34:56,151
No. I'm sorry. I'm sorry. It is funny.

606
00:34:56,271 --> 00:34:58,431
It's a hoot
that you don't get why we need this.

607
00:34:58,591 --> 00:35:00,750
Tony, maybe this might not be the time.

608
00:35:00,910 --> 00:35:03,230
Really? That's it?

609
00:35:03,350 --> 00:35:04,607
You just roll over, show your belly

610
00:35:04,631 --> 00:35:06,311
every time somebody snarls?

611
00:35:06,470 --> 00:35:07,847
Only when I've created a murder bot.

612
00:35:07,871 --> 00:35:10,070
We didn't. We weren't even close.

613
00:35:10,190 --> 00:35:11,391
Were we close to an interface?

614
00:35:11,511 --> 00:35:15,111
Well, you did something right.
And you did it right here.

615
00:35:15,151 --> 00:35:17,166
The Avengers were supposed to
be different than S.H.I.E.L.D.

616
00:35:17,190 --> 00:35:20,150
Anybody remember when I carried
a nuke through a wormhole?

617
00:35:20,310 --> 00:35:21,967
- No, it's never come up.
- STARK: Saved New York?

618
00:35:21,991 --> 00:35:23,910
RHODES: Never heard that.
STARK: Recall that?

619
00:35:24,031 --> 00:35:27,711
A hostile alien army came
charging through a hole in space.

620
00:35:28,351 --> 00:35:30,510
We're standing 300 feet below it.

621
00:35:32,190 --> 00:35:33,670
We're the Avengers.

622
00:35:33,831 --> 00:35:35,910
We can bust arms dealers
all the livelong day,

623
00:35:36,030 --> 00:35:38,271
but that up there, that's...

624
00:35:38,990 --> 00:35:40,911
That's the endgame.

625
00:35:41,511 --> 00:35:43,390
How were you guys
planning on beating that?

626
00:35:44,311 --> 00:35:45,710
Together.

627
00:35:49,070 --> 00:35:50,431
We'll lose.

628
00:35:51,510 --> 00:35:53,430
Then we'll do that together, too.

629
00:35:56,350 --> 00:35:58,670
Thor's right. Ultron's calling us out.

630
00:35:59,550 --> 00:36:01,510
And I'd like to find him
before he's ready for us.

631
00:36:02,710 --> 00:36:04,310
The world's a big place.

632
00:36:04,510 --> 00:36:06,430
Let's start making it smaller.

633
00:36:14,990 --> 00:36:16,551
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

634
00:36:29,550 --> 00:36:31,590
WANDA: Talk,
and if you are wasting our time...

635
00:36:31,710 --> 00:36:36,070
ULTRON: Did you know this church is
in the exact center of the city?

636
00:36:36,231 --> 00:36:38,230
The elders decreed it so that everyone

637
00:36:38,390 --> 00:36:40,830
could be equally close to God.

638
00:36:41,350 --> 00:36:42,510
I like that.

639
00:36:43,030 --> 00:36:44,950
The geometry of belief.

640
00:36:47,070 --> 00:36:49,470
You're wondering
why you can't look inside my head.

641
00:36:49,910 --> 00:36:51,870
Sometimes it's hard.

642
00:36:52,030 --> 00:36:54,350
But sooner or later,
every man shows himself.

643
00:36:56,070 --> 00:36:57,390
Oh, I'm sure they do.

644
00:36:58,510 --> 00:37:00,910
But you needed
something more than a man.

645
00:37:01,750 --> 00:37:04,270
That's why you let
Stark take the scepter.

646
00:37:04,670 --> 00:37:05,670
I didn't expect,

647
00:37:08,190 --> 00:37:10,110
but I saw Stark's fear.

648
00:37:10,750 --> 00:37:11,989
I knew it would control him.

649
00:37:12,109 --> 00:37:13,950
Make him self-destruct.

650
00:37:14,110 --> 00:37:16,430
Everyone creates the thing they dread.

651
00:37:17,270 --> 00:37:19,870
Men of peace create engines of war.

652
00:37:20,390 --> 00:37:22,590
Invaders create Avengers.

653
00:37:22,790 --> 00:37:24,230
People create

654
00:37:25,790 --> 00:37:27,789
smaller people? Uh...

655
00:37:27,909 --> 00:37:30,989
"Children." (CHUCKLES)
I lost the word, there.

656
00:37:31,109 --> 00:37:32,470
Children

657
00:37:32,630 --> 00:37:34,869
designed to supplant them,

658
00:37:34,989 --> 00:37:37,789
to help them end.

659
00:37:38,550 --> 00:37:40,589
Is that why you've come,

660
00:37:40,749 --> 00:37:41,830
to end the Avengers?

661
00:37:41,950 --> 00:37:44,269
I've come to save the world.

662
00:37:44,990 --> 00:37:47,589
But also... Yeah.

663
00:37:51,790 --> 00:37:53,469
We'll move out right away.

664
00:37:53,589 --> 00:37:55,110
This is a start, but there's something

665
00:37:55,230 --> 00:37:56,749
we need to begin the real work.

666
00:37:57,149 --> 00:37:58,870
- All of these are...
- ULTRON: Me.

667
00:37:59,550 --> 00:38:02,950
I have what the Avengers
never will. Harmony.

668
00:38:03,109 --> 00:38:05,310
They're discordant. Disconnected.

669
00:38:05,470 --> 00:38:07,309
Stark's already got them
turning on each other.

670
00:38:07,469 --> 00:38:09,829
And when you get inside
the rest of their heads...

671
00:38:09,949 --> 00:38:12,110
Everyone's plan is not to kill them.

672
00:38:12,230 --> 00:38:13,709
And make them martyrs?

673
00:38:14,349 --> 00:38:15,910
You need patience.

674
00:38:16,069 --> 00:38:17,749
Need to see the big picture.

675
00:38:17,910 --> 00:38:21,150
I don't see the big picture.
I have a little picture.

676
00:38:22,349 --> 00:38:23,949
I take it out and look at it,

677
00:38:24,830 --> 00:38:25,909
every day.

678
00:38:26,109 --> 00:38:28,869
You lost your parents in the
bombings. I've seen the records.

679
00:38:29,029 --> 00:38:30,245
The records are not the picture.

680
00:38:30,269 --> 00:38:32,669
- Pietro.
- No, please.

681
00:38:35,789 --> 00:38:38,909
We were 10 years old.
Having dinner, the four of us.

682
00:38:40,509 --> 00:38:42,349
When the first shell hits,
two floors below,

683
00:38:42,509 --> 00:38:44,510
it makes a hole in the floor.

684
00:38:44,710 --> 00:38:46,189
It's big.

685
00:38:47,630 --> 00:38:49,389
Our parents go in

686
00:38:49,549 --> 00:38:52,589
and the whole building
starts coming apart.

687
00:38:53,309 --> 00:38:54,829
I grab her,

688
00:38:55,509 --> 00:38:57,630
roll under the bed,
and the second shell hits.

689
00:38:57,989 --> 00:38:59,909
But it doesn't go off.

690
00:39:01,949 --> 00:39:03,589
It just

691
00:39:04,109 --> 00:39:06,029
sits there in the rubble.

692
00:39:07,070 --> 00:39:09,309
Three feet from our faces.

693
00:39:10,390 --> 00:39:12,389
And on the side of the shell

694
00:39:12,509 --> 00:39:13,869
is painted one word.

695
00:39:14,069 --> 00:39:15,709
"Stark."

696
00:39:17,549 --> 00:39:19,709
PIETRO: We were trapped for two days.

697
00:39:20,149 --> 00:39:21,949
Every effort to save us,

698
00:39:22,069 --> 00:39:23,629
every shift in the bricks,

699
00:39:23,829 --> 00:39:26,109
I think, "This will set it off."

700
00:39:29,389 --> 00:39:30,829
We wait for two days

701
00:39:30,949 --> 00:39:33,229
for Tony Stark to kill us.

702
00:39:35,749 --> 00:39:37,589
I know what they are.

703
00:39:38,749 --> 00:39:42,509
I wondered why only you two
survived Strucker's experiments.

704
00:39:43,509 --> 00:39:44,669
Now I don't.

705
00:39:45,069 --> 00:39:46,789
We will make it right.

706
00:39:47,269 --> 00:39:48,749
You and I can hurt them.

707
00:39:50,229 --> 00:39:53,509
But you will tear them apart

708
00:39:55,508 --> 00:39:57,349
<i>from the inside.</i>

709
00:40:03,949 --> 00:40:05,148
He's all over the globe.

710
00:40:05,268 --> 00:40:08,468
Robotics labs, weapons facilities,
jet propulsion labs.

711
00:40:08,588 --> 00:40:10,629
Reports of a metal man, or men,

712
00:40:10,789 --> 00:40:12,669
coming in and emptying the place.

713
00:40:12,789 --> 00:40:13,949
Fatalities?

714
00:40:14,069 --> 00:40:15,148
Only when engaged.

715
00:40:15,268 --> 00:40:16,909
Mostly guys left in a fugue state

716
00:40:17,029 --> 00:40:19,309
going on about
old memories, worst fears,

717
00:40:19,469 --> 00:40:21,628
and "something too fast to see."

718
00:40:21,748 --> 00:40:23,149
ROGERS: Maximoffs.

719
00:40:23,429 --> 00:40:24,644
That makes sense he'd go to them.

720
00:40:24,668 --> 00:40:26,109
They have someone in common.

721
00:40:26,269 --> 00:40:28,188
Not anymore.

722
00:40:32,068 --> 00:40:33,949
That's a negative. I answer to you.

723
00:40:35,308 --> 00:40:36,349
Yes, ma'am.

724
00:40:36,469 --> 00:40:38,268
Barton. Might have something.

725
00:40:38,829 --> 00:40:39,869
I gotta go.

726
00:40:39,989 --> 00:40:41,148
Who was that?

727
00:40:41,948 --> 00:40:43,189
Girlfriend.

728
00:40:45,949 --> 00:40:47,068
STARK: What's this?

729
00:40:47,228 --> 00:40:49,429
A message. Ultron killed Strucker.

730
00:40:50,948 --> 00:40:53,668
And he did a Banksy
at the crime scene, just for us.

731
00:40:53,828 --> 00:40:55,229
ROMANOFF: This is a smoke screen.

732
00:40:55,349 --> 00:40:57,748
Why send a message
when you've just given a speech?

733
00:40:57,868 --> 00:41:00,228
Strucker knew something
that Ultron wanted us to miss.

734
00:41:00,388 --> 00:41:02,149
Yeah, I bet he... Yeah.

735
00:41:02,829 --> 00:41:04,548
Everything we had
on Strucker's been erased.

736
00:41:04,908 --> 00:41:06,188
ROGERS: Not everything.

737
00:41:07,788 --> 00:41:09,428
Known associates.

738
00:41:09,948 --> 00:41:11,508
Baron Strucker had a lot of friends.

739
00:41:11,669 --> 00:41:13,364
BANNER: Well,
these people are all horrible.

740
00:41:13,388 --> 00:41:15,109
Wait. I know that guy.

741
00:41:17,588 --> 00:41:19,244
From back in the day.
He operates off the African coast.

742
00:41:19,268 --> 00:41:20,268
Black market arms.

743
00:41:21,509 --> 00:41:23,468
There are conventions.
All right? You meet people.

744
00:41:23,508 --> 00:41:24,869
I didn't sell him anything.

745
00:41:25,708 --> 00:41:27,844
He was talking about finding
something new, a game-changer.

746
00:41:27,868 --> 00:41:29,188
It was all very Ahab.

747
00:41:29,988 --> 00:41:31,108
This?

748
00:41:31,269 --> 00:41:32,364
Ah, it's a tattoo, I don't think he had it.

749
00:41:32,388 --> 00:41:34,749
THOR: Those are tattoos,
this is a brand.

750
00:41:36,428 --> 00:41:39,908
Oh, yeah. It's a word
in an African dialect meaning "thief."

751
00:41:40,508 --> 00:41:41,868
In a much less friendly way.

752
00:41:42,148 --> 00:41:43,908
- What dialect?
- Wakanada.

753
00:41:44,028 --> 00:41:45,748
(STAMMERING) Wakanda.

754
00:41:47,348 --> 00:41:48,524
If this guy got out of Wakanda

755
00:41:48,548 --> 00:41:49,868
with some of their trade goods...

756
00:41:49,948 --> 00:41:51,204
I thought your father
said he got the last of it.

757
00:41:51,228 --> 00:41:52,348
I don't follow.

758
00:41:52,468 --> 00:41:54,148
What comes out of Wakanda?

759
00:41:55,948 --> 00:41:57,868
STARK: The strongest metal on Earth.

760
00:41:59,228 --> 00:42:00,548
Where is this guy now?

761
00:42:14,588 --> 00:42:16,268
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

762
00:42:25,948 --> 00:42:27,748
KLAUE: Don't tell me
your men swindled you.

763
00:42:27,908 --> 00:42:30,388
I sent you six short-range heat-seekers

764
00:42:30,508 --> 00:42:33,067
and got a boat full of rusted parts.

765
00:42:33,187 --> 00:42:34,428
Now, you will make it right,

766
00:42:34,588 --> 00:42:37,748
or the next missile I send you
will come very much faster.

767
00:42:39,667 --> 00:42:42,108
Now, minister, where were we?

768
00:42:42,268 --> 00:42:43,748
(MACHINES POWERING DOWN)

769
00:42:44,828 --> 00:42:46,267
(WORKERS CLAMORING)

770
00:43:11,108 --> 00:43:12,107
(SIGHS)

771
00:43:13,748 --> 00:43:16,628
KLAUE: Yeah. The Enhanced.

772
00:43:17,348 --> 00:43:18,987
Strucker's prize pupils.

773
00:43:22,147 --> 00:43:23,788
Do you want a candy? Hmm?

774
00:43:25,307 --> 00:43:27,907
I was sorry to hear about Strucker.

775
00:43:28,027 --> 00:43:31,027
But then, he knew what kind of
world he was helping create.

776
00:43:31,627 --> 00:43:34,027
Human life. Not a growth market.

777
00:43:36,748 --> 00:43:38,387
You didn't know?

778
00:43:38,827 --> 00:43:42,307
Is this your first time
intimidating someone?

779
00:43:42,628 --> 00:43:45,147
I'm afraid I'm not that afraid.

780
00:43:45,307 --> 00:43:47,627
Everybody is afraid of something.

781
00:43:47,747 --> 00:43:48,747
Cuttlefish.

782
00:43:50,067 --> 00:43:51,427
Deep sea fish.

783
00:43:51,507 --> 00:43:53,148
They make lights, disco lights...

784
00:43:53,347 --> 00:43:54,547
(IMITATES CUTTLEFISH)

785
00:43:54,827 --> 00:43:56,667
to hypnotize their prey, and then...

786
00:43:57,947 --> 00:44:00,107
I saw a documentary. It was terrifying.

787
00:44:05,548 --> 00:44:08,107
So if you're going to fiddle with my brain

788
00:44:09,068 --> 00:44:11,267
and make me see a giant cuttlefish,

789
00:44:11,547 --> 00:44:13,627
then I know you don't do business.

790
00:44:13,787 --> 00:44:16,067
And I know you're not in charge.

791
00:44:16,267 --> 00:44:17,547
And I only deal

792
00:44:18,668 --> 00:44:20,267
with the man in charge.

793
00:44:20,747 --> 00:44:22,028
- (GLASS SHATTERING)
- (GROANS)

794
00:44:25,307 --> 00:44:27,707
There is no man in charge.

795
00:44:30,707 --> 00:44:32,387
Let's talk business.

796
00:44:45,347 --> 00:44:48,627
ULTRON: Upon this rock,
I will build my church.

797
00:44:50,387 --> 00:44:51,667
Vibranium.

798
00:44:52,827 --> 00:44:53,827
KLAUE: You know,

799
00:44:54,226 --> 00:44:57,227
it came at great personal cost.

800
00:44:57,626 --> 00:44:59,227
It's worth billions.

801
00:44:59,347 --> 00:45:00,387
(CHUCKLES)

802
00:45:03,587 --> 00:45:04,627
Now so are you.

803
00:45:04,827 --> 00:45:05,907
(CELL PHONE BUZZING)

804
00:45:06,027 --> 00:45:07,586
It's all under your dummy holdings.

805
00:45:07,707 --> 00:45:09,707
Finance is so weird.

806
00:45:11,227 --> 00:45:12,387
But I always say,

807
00:45:12,427 --> 00:45:14,587
"Keep your friends rich
and your enemies rich

808
00:45:14,747 --> 00:45:16,547
"and wait to find out which is which."

809
00:45:19,427 --> 00:45:20,466
Stark.

810
00:45:21,867 --> 00:45:22,987
What?

811
00:45:23,186 --> 00:45:24,907
Tony Stark used to say that.

812
00:45:26,506 --> 00:45:27,547
To me.

813
00:45:28,427 --> 00:45:29,586
You're one of his.

814
00:45:29,946 --> 00:45:31,587
What? I'm not...

815
00:45:32,307 --> 00:45:33,426
- (GRUNTS)
- (GROANS)

816
00:45:33,907 --> 00:45:34,947
I'm not.

817
00:45:35,107 --> 00:45:36,586
You think I'm one of Stark's puppets?

818
00:45:36,746 --> 00:45:37,827
His hollow men?

819
00:45:38,267 --> 00:45:40,467
I mean, look at me.
Do I look like Iron Man?

820
00:45:40,667 --> 00:45:41,947
- Stark is nothing!
- (GROANS)

821
00:45:43,706 --> 00:45:45,906
I'm sorry. I'm... Oh!

822
00:45:46,026 --> 00:45:48,027
I'm sure that's gonna be okay. I'm sorry.

823
00:45:48,147 --> 00:45:49,826
It's just that I don't understand.

824
00:45:49,946 --> 00:45:52,226
Don't compare me with Stark!

825
00:45:52,466 --> 00:45:54,267
(GROANING)

826
00:45:54,987 --> 00:45:56,146
ULTRON: It's a thing with me.

827
00:45:56,266 --> 00:45:58,107
Stark is... He's a sickness!

828
00:45:58,307 --> 00:45:59,946
STARK: Ah, Junior.

829
00:46:01,826 --> 00:46:03,386
You're gonna break
your old man's heart.

830
00:46:04,667 --> 00:46:05,706
If I have to.

831
00:46:08,066 --> 00:46:09,466
THOR: Nobody has to break anything.

832
00:46:09,546 --> 00:46:11,267
ULTRON: Clearly you've never
made an omelet.

833
00:46:11,386 --> 00:46:12,586
He beat me by one second.

834
00:46:13,787 --> 00:46:15,146
PIETRO: Ah, yes. He's funny.

835
00:46:15,506 --> 00:46:16,907
Mr. Stark.

836
00:46:17,826 --> 00:46:19,386
It's what? Comfortable?

837
00:46:21,026 --> 00:46:22,306
Like old times?

838
00:46:22,666 --> 00:46:23,667
This was never my life.

839
00:46:23,827 --> 00:46:25,202
You two can still walk away from this.

840
00:46:25,226 --> 00:46:26,667
Oh, we will.

841
00:46:26,867 --> 00:46:28,546
- I know you've suffered.
- (ULTRON SCOFFS)

842
00:46:28,786 --> 00:46:30,187
(CHUCKLES) Captain America.

843
00:46:30,866 --> 00:46:33,307
God's righteous man.

844
00:46:33,467 --> 00:46:35,746
Pretending you could live without a war.

845
00:46:36,547 --> 00:46:39,507
I can't physically
throw up in my mouth, but...

846
00:46:39,667 --> 00:46:41,746
If you believe in peace,
then let us keep it.

847
00:46:42,186 --> 00:46:45,506
I think you're confusing
"peace" with "quiet."

848
00:46:45,666 --> 00:46:47,426
Uh-huh. What's the vibranium for?

849
00:46:47,746 --> 00:46:48,746
I'm glad you asked that,

850
00:46:48,826 --> 00:46:52,586
because I wanted to take this time
to explain my evil plan.

851
00:47:10,426 --> 00:47:11,546
(PANTING)

852
00:47:12,146 --> 00:47:13,706
- Shoot them.
- Which ones?

853
00:47:14,066 --> 00:47:15,226
All of them!

854
00:47:15,386 --> 00:47:16,666
HENCHMAN: Move! Move! Move!

855
00:47:16,906 --> 00:47:18,426
(GUNFIRE)

856
00:47:22,426 --> 00:47:23,466
(BOTH GRUNTING)

857
00:47:43,706 --> 00:47:44,985
Oh. (YELPS)

858
00:47:47,546 --> 00:47:48,586
(GROANS)

859
00:47:55,906 --> 00:47:57,226
(GRUNTING)

860
00:48:03,586 --> 00:48:05,426
(GROANS)

861
00:48:05,626 --> 00:48:06,786
- Stay down, kid.
- (GUNFIRE)

862
00:48:09,186 --> 00:48:11,626
It's time for some mind games.

863
00:48:13,026 --> 00:48:15,266
Guys? Is this a code green?

864
00:48:15,426 --> 00:48:16,825
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

865
00:48:31,146 --> 00:48:32,785
Thor, status.

866
00:48:32,825 --> 00:48:34,266
The girl tried to warp my mind.

867
00:48:34,426 --> 00:48:35,706
- (GROANS)
- Take special care.

868
00:48:35,825 --> 00:48:37,906
I doubt a human could keep her at bay.

869
00:48:38,346 --> 00:48:41,346
Fortunately, I am mighty.

870
00:48:46,665 --> 00:48:48,026
(GRUNTING)

871
00:48:50,025 --> 00:48:51,106
(GROANS)

872
00:49:01,026 --> 00:49:03,305
ULTRON: This is going very well.

873
00:49:05,345 --> 00:49:06,505
(RAPID BEEPING)

874
00:49:12,945 --> 00:49:14,226
- (GRUNTS)
- (GASPS)

875
00:49:14,905 --> 00:49:16,465
I've done the whole mind control thing.

876
00:49:17,266 --> 00:49:18,265
Not a fan.

877
00:49:19,385 --> 00:49:20,506
(YELPS)

878
00:49:25,905 --> 00:49:27,865
Yeah, you better run.

879
00:49:29,585 --> 00:49:31,385
BARTON: <i>Who's ever standing,
we got to move!</i>

880
00:49:33,466 --> 00:49:34,505
<i>Guys?</i>

881
00:49:52,265 --> 00:49:53,545
Again.

882
00:49:53,865 --> 00:49:55,065
You'll break them.

883
00:49:55,585 --> 00:49:57,265
MADAME B: Only the breakable ones.

884
00:49:57,825 --> 00:49:59,265
You're made of marble.

885
00:49:59,705 --> 00:50:01,865
We'll celebrate
after the graduation ceremony.

886
00:50:02,785 --> 00:50:03,905
ROMANOFF: What if I fail?

887
00:50:08,185 --> 00:50:09,224
(WHIMPERING)

888
00:50:09,545 --> 00:50:10,785
You never fail.

889
00:50:12,705 --> 00:50:14,385
- (SWING MUSIC PLAYING)
- (PEOPLE LAUGHING)

890
00:50:27,625 --> 00:50:28,784
(GRUNTING)

891
00:50:33,665 --> 00:50:35,585
Are you ready for our dance?

892
00:50:37,825 --> 00:50:39,145
(GROWLING)

893
00:50:40,425 --> 00:50:41,624
(BUBBLING)

894
00:50:44,744 --> 00:50:45,785
HEIMDALL: Is it him?

895
00:50:46,145 --> 00:50:47,984
Is that the first son of Odin?

896
00:50:48,584 --> 00:50:50,065
- Heimdall, your eyes.
- Oh.

897
00:50:50,744 --> 00:50:52,625
They see everything.

898
00:50:52,985 --> 00:50:55,265
They see you leading us to Hel.

899
00:50:56,385 --> 00:50:57,624
- Wake up!
- (CHOKING)

900
00:50:58,665 --> 00:50:59,945
(SWING MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING)

901
00:51:00,624 --> 00:51:02,585
The war is over, Steve.

902
00:51:02,985 --> 00:51:04,264
We can go home.

903
00:51:06,105 --> 00:51:07,304
Imagine it.

904
00:51:16,624 --> 00:51:18,144
I can still save you!

905
00:51:18,505 --> 00:51:21,785
We're all dead! Can you not see?

906
00:51:21,905 --> 00:51:23,184
(GRUNTING)

907
00:51:26,544 --> 00:51:28,785
You're a destroyer, Odinson.

908
00:51:29,344 --> 00:51:30,464
(GROANING)

909
00:51:31,945 --> 00:51:33,944
HEIMDALL: See
where your power leads.

910
00:51:34,504 --> 00:51:35,704
(SCREAMING)

911
00:51:35,944 --> 00:51:36,944
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

912
00:51:42,144 --> 00:51:43,624
(BOTH GRUNTING)

913
00:51:44,985 --> 00:51:46,104
Sloppy.

914
00:51:46,544 --> 00:51:47,584
(PANTING)

915
00:51:47,785 --> 00:51:48,824
Pretending to fail.

916
00:51:49,824 --> 00:51:51,145
The ceremony is necessary

917
00:51:52,464 --> 00:51:54,385
for you to take your place in the world.

918
00:51:55,384 --> 00:51:56,544
I have no place in the world.

919
00:51:56,704 --> 00:51:57,745
MADAME B: Exactly.

920
00:52:02,584 --> 00:52:03,664
PIETRO: What can I do?

921
00:52:03,824 --> 00:52:04,904
(GROANS) It hurts.

922
00:52:06,144 --> 00:52:07,184
I'm going to kill him.

923
00:52:07,304 --> 00:52:08,504
- I'll be right back.
- No.

924
00:52:08,664 --> 00:52:09,984
(PANTING) I'm all right.

925
00:52:10,865 --> 00:52:11,984
I want...

926
00:52:14,944 --> 00:52:16,824
I want to finish the plan.

927
00:52:17,664 --> 00:52:19,344
I want the big one.

928
00:52:30,264 --> 00:52:31,984
Uh, the vibranium is getting away.

929
00:52:32,944 --> 00:52:34,264
And you're not going anywhere.

930
00:52:34,384 --> 00:52:37,184
Of course not. I'm already there.

931
00:52:37,344 --> 00:52:38,344
You'll catch on.

932
00:52:38,464 --> 00:52:40,864
But first, you might need
to catch Dr. Banner.

933
00:52:47,064 --> 00:52:48,544
(GROWLING)

934
00:52:55,664 --> 00:52:57,544
News or footage. Keyword, "Hulk."

935
00:52:57,704 --> 00:52:59,223
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)
- (BEEPING)

936
00:53:02,384 --> 00:53:04,184
<i>Natasha, I could really use a lullaby.</i>

937
00:53:04,304 --> 00:53:05,783
- (PANTING)
- That's not gonna happen.

938
00:53:05,863 --> 00:53:07,344
Not for a while.

939
00:53:07,944 --> 00:53:09,623
<i>The whole team is down.</i>

940
00:53:10,104 --> 00:53:11,224
<i>You got no backup here.</i>

941
00:53:12,423 --> 00:53:13,704
I'm calling in Veronica.

942
00:53:16,183 --> 00:53:17,344
(POWERING UP)

943
00:53:20,464 --> 00:53:22,103
(SIRENS WAILING)

944
00:53:24,144 --> 00:53:25,223
(OFFICER EXCLAIMS)

945
00:53:25,263 --> 00:53:26,744
DRIVER: We need backup!

946
00:53:28,943 --> 00:53:30,264
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

947
00:53:33,304 --> 00:53:34,384
(GRUNTS)

948
00:53:41,063 --> 00:53:42,584
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

949
00:53:44,144 --> 00:53:46,144
- (BULLETS RICOCHETING)
- (ROARING)

950
00:54:02,023 --> 00:54:03,264
(POUNDING)

951
00:54:05,784 --> 00:54:07,143
Go! Keep moving!

952
00:54:08,784 --> 00:54:09,824
(GUNS COCKING)

953
00:54:10,863 --> 00:54:12,264
- (GROWLS)
- (POUNDS)

954
00:54:12,864 --> 00:54:14,943
- (CAR ALARMS BLARING)
- (POUNDING CONTINUES)

955
00:54:20,743 --> 00:54:21,783
(ROARING)

956
00:54:23,623 --> 00:54:24,983
(RUMBLING)

957
00:54:30,423 --> 00:54:31,623
- (ROARING)
- (SCREAMING)

958
00:54:46,503 --> 00:54:48,663
All right, everybody, stand down!

959
00:54:49,863 --> 00:54:50,983
(GROWLING)

960
00:54:54,983 --> 00:54:56,263
<i>Will you listen to me?</i>

961
00:54:56,623 --> 00:54:59,023
That little witch is
messing with your mind.

962
00:54:59,143 --> 00:55:01,383
You're stronger than her.
You're smarter than her.

963
00:55:01,503 --> 00:55:03,703
- You're Bruce Banner.
- (ROARING)

964
00:55:03,863 --> 00:55:05,559
Right, right, right,
don't mention puny Banner.

965
00:55:05,583 --> 00:55:06,663
(GRUNTS)

966
00:55:10,623 --> 00:55:11,663
<i>Okay!</i>

967
00:55:33,382 --> 00:55:34,663
In the back?

968
00:55:34,783 --> 00:55:35,783
Dick move, Banner.

969
00:55:42,703 --> 00:55:43,983
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

970
00:55:47,263 --> 00:55:48,783
- (BEEPING)
- Veronica, give me a hand.

971
00:56:09,062 --> 00:56:10,263
(GASPS)

972
00:56:11,463 --> 00:56:12,582
(ROARING)

973
00:56:16,703 --> 00:56:18,223
Go to sleep, go to sleep, go to sleep.

974
00:56:19,222 --> 00:56:20,423
(GROWLING)

975
00:56:27,543 --> 00:56:29,222
Okay, pal, we're gonna
get you out of town.

976
00:56:31,382 --> 00:56:32,502
Not that way, not that way.

977
00:56:41,062 --> 00:56:42,943
Come on, Bruce!
You gotta work with me.

978
00:56:44,222 --> 00:56:45,622
- (HISSING)
- (ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

979
00:56:45,782 --> 00:56:46,783
(PEOPLE EXCLAIM)

980
00:56:50,343 --> 00:56:51,702
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

981
00:56:51,822 --> 00:56:52,983
(YELPS)

982
00:56:56,463 --> 00:56:57,502
<i>Everybody, out!</i>

983
00:57:00,023 --> 00:57:01,302
(ROARING)

984
00:57:04,462 --> 00:57:05,742
<i>Going down?</i>

985
00:57:12,503 --> 00:57:13,582
(SPITS)

986
00:57:15,262 --> 00:57:16,502
I'm sorry.

987
00:57:19,422 --> 00:57:20,662
(GRUNTING)

988
00:57:30,622 --> 00:57:32,342
- Damage report?
- (STATIC)

989
00:57:32,502 --> 00:57:34,782
That's comprehensive.
Show me something.

990
00:57:44,182 --> 00:57:45,342
(BEEPING)

991
00:57:46,502 --> 00:57:47,982
How quickly can we buy this building?

992
00:57:54,422 --> 00:57:56,142
(SCREAMING)

993
00:58:20,421 --> 00:58:22,422
SOLDIER 1: Move! Move! Move!
SOLDIER 2: Go, go, go!

994
00:58:25,502 --> 00:58:26,782
SOLDIER 3: Flank him, flank him!

995
00:58:31,422 --> 00:58:33,461
(ROARS)

996
00:58:33,861 --> 00:58:35,702
(GROANING)

997
00:58:39,622 --> 00:58:40,902
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

998
00:58:41,102 --> 00:58:42,382
(SIRENS WAILING)

999
00:58:56,621 --> 00:58:57,782
(COCKS)

1000
00:59:16,261 --> 00:59:18,301
HILL ON RADIO: <i>The news
is loving you guys.</i>

1001
00:59:19,421 --> 00:59:21,022
<i>Nobody else is.</i>

1002
00:59:21,501 --> 00:59:23,662
There's been no official call
for Banner's arrest

1003
00:59:23,782 --> 00:59:25,941
<i>but it's in the air.</i>

1004
00:59:26,501 --> 00:59:27,638
STARK: The Stark Relief Foundation?

1005
00:59:27,662 --> 00:59:28,981
HILL: <i>Already on the scene.</i>

1006
00:59:29,101 --> 00:59:31,941
<i>- How's the team?</i>
- STARK: Everyone's...

1007
00:59:32,341 --> 00:59:34,861
We took a hit. We'll shake it off.

1008
00:59:35,341 --> 00:59:37,581
HILL: <i>Well, for now,
I'd stay in stealth mode</i>

1009
00:59:37,701 --> 00:59:38,901
<i>and stay away from here.</i>

1010
00:59:40,342 --> 00:59:41,861
So, run and hide?

1011
00:59:42,621 --> 00:59:44,021
<i>Until we can find Ultron,</i>

1012
00:59:44,141 --> 00:59:46,942
<i>I don't have a lot else to offer.</i>

1013
00:59:47,101 --> 00:59:48,981
(SIGHS) Neither do we.

1014
00:59:53,222 --> 00:59:54,421
(SIGHS)

1015
00:59:55,701 --> 00:59:57,301
Hey, you wanna switch out?

1016
00:59:57,501 --> 00:59:58,741
No, I'm good.

1017
00:59:59,261 --> 01:00:01,141
If you wanna get some kip,
now's a good time

1018
01:00:01,301 --> 01:00:02,781
because we're still a few hours out.

1019
01:00:02,902 --> 01:00:04,461
Few hours from where?

1020
01:00:05,381 --> 01:00:06,661
A safe house.

1021
01:00:33,141 --> 01:00:34,621
What is this place?

1022
01:00:34,741 --> 01:00:36,101
Safe house.

1023
01:00:37,061 --> 01:00:38,261
Let's hope.

1024
01:00:43,301 --> 01:00:44,341
Honey?

1025
01:00:44,901 --> 01:00:46,061
I'm home.

1026
01:00:48,660 --> 01:00:49,701
Hi.

1027
01:00:50,061 --> 01:00:52,101
Company. Sorry, didn't call ahead.

1028
01:00:52,221 --> 01:00:53,221
Hey.

1029
01:00:54,181 --> 01:00:55,701
This is an agent of some kind.

1030
01:00:55,741 --> 01:00:58,180
Gentlemen, this is Laura.

1031
01:00:59,181 --> 01:01:01,020
I know all of your names. (CHUCKLES)

1032
01:01:02,661 --> 01:01:04,700
- (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)
- Ooh. Incoming.

1033
01:01:05,621 --> 01:01:07,301
- Dad!
- Hi, sweetheart!

1034
01:01:07,460 --> 01:01:08,581
Hey, buddy.

1035
01:01:08,821 --> 01:01:10,181
How are you guys doing?

1036
01:01:10,461 --> 01:01:12,517
- These are smaller agents.
- BARTON: Look at your face!

1037
01:01:12,541 --> 01:01:13,621
Oh, my goodness.

1038
01:01:14,020 --> 01:01:16,381
- LILA: Did you bring Auntie Nat?
- (BARTON GASPS)

1039
01:01:16,621 --> 01:01:19,701
- Why don't you hug her and find out?
- (BARTON LAUGHING)

1040
01:01:20,500 --> 01:01:22,837
- Sorry for barging in on you.
- Yeah, we would have called ahead,

1041
01:01:22,861 --> 01:01:24,901
but we were busy having
no idea that you existed.

1042
01:01:25,221 --> 01:01:28,181
Yeah, well, Fury helped me
set this up when I joined.

1043
01:01:29,021 --> 01:01:30,196
He kept it off S.H.I.E.L.D.'s files.

1044
01:01:30,220 --> 01:01:31,661
I'd like to keep it that way.

1045
01:01:32,421 --> 01:01:34,140
I figure it's a good place to lay low.

1046
01:01:34,260 --> 01:01:35,741
- LAURA: Honey.
- (CRUNCHING)

1047
01:01:36,780 --> 01:01:39,261
I missed you. How's little Natasha, huh?

1048
01:01:39,381 --> 01:01:40,700
LAURA: She's...

1049
01:01:42,980 --> 01:01:43,980
Nathaniel.

1050
01:01:46,740 --> 01:01:47,740
Traitor.

1051
01:01:48,901 --> 01:01:50,900
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

1052
01:01:56,500 --> 01:01:57,580
(DINGS)

1053
01:02:03,620 --> 01:02:04,781
Thor?

1054
01:02:04,901 --> 01:02:06,740
I saw something in that dream.

1055
01:02:06,900 --> 01:02:09,460
I need answers. I won't find them here.

1056
01:02:20,020 --> 01:02:21,300
PEGGY: <i>We can go home.</i>

1057
01:02:27,381 --> 01:02:28,620
(SIGHS)

1058
01:02:32,820 --> 01:02:34,660
See? You worried for nothing.

1059
01:02:34,780 --> 01:02:36,900
Can't even feel the difference, can you?

1060
01:02:39,300 --> 01:02:40,461
If they're sleeping here,

1061
01:02:40,620 --> 01:02:42,460
some of them
are gonna have to double up.

1062
01:02:42,580 --> 01:02:44,420
(LAUGHING)

1063
01:02:44,540 --> 01:02:46,660
Yeah, that's not gonna sell.

1064
01:02:49,500 --> 01:02:51,860
What about Nat and Dr. Banner?

1065
01:02:52,260 --> 01:02:54,180
How long has that been going on?

1066
01:02:54,740 --> 01:02:56,740
- Has what?
- (LAUGHING)

1067
01:02:56,900 --> 01:02:58,660
You are so cute.

1068
01:02:58,860 --> 01:03:00,300
Nat and Banner?

1069
01:03:01,020 --> 01:03:02,420
I'll explain when you're older,

1070
01:03:02,660 --> 01:03:05,300
- Hawkeye.
- Well, okay.

1071
01:03:07,260 --> 01:03:08,660
It's bad, right?

1072
01:03:09,020 --> 01:03:10,180
Nat seems really shaken.

1073
01:03:10,420 --> 01:03:11,540
(SIGHS)

1074
01:03:11,660 --> 01:03:13,140
Ultron has these allies.

1075
01:03:13,300 --> 01:03:15,500
These, uh, kids.

1076
01:03:15,620 --> 01:03:17,220
They're punks, really.

1077
01:03:18,900 --> 01:03:21,340
But they carry a big, damn stick.

1078
01:03:21,460 --> 01:03:22,659
And Nat took a serious hit.

1079
01:03:23,860 --> 01:03:26,340
Someone's gonna have to
teach them some manners.

1080
01:03:26,540 --> 01:03:28,340
That someone being you.

1081
01:03:29,660 --> 01:03:32,499
You know
I totally support your avenging.

1082
01:03:32,619 --> 01:03:34,460
I couldn't be prouder.

1083
01:03:36,020 --> 01:03:37,340
But I see those guys...

1084
01:03:37,540 --> 01:03:39,500
Those gods...

1085
01:03:41,500 --> 01:03:43,220
You don't think they need me.

1086
01:03:43,900 --> 01:03:47,580
I think they do, which is a lot scarier.

1087
01:03:48,699 --> 01:03:50,540
- They're a mess.
- (SIGHING)

1088
01:03:51,539 --> 01:03:52,540
BARTON: Yeah.

1089
01:03:53,260 --> 01:03:54,699
I guess they're my mess.

1090
01:03:56,260 --> 01:03:57,859
You need to be sure

1091
01:03:58,339 --> 01:04:00,979
that this team is really a team,

1092
01:04:01,099 --> 01:04:02,780
and that they have your back.

1093
01:04:06,180 --> 01:04:08,699
Things are changing for us.

1094
01:04:08,820 --> 01:04:11,219
In a few months' time,

1095
01:04:11,379 --> 01:04:14,139
you and me are gonna be outnumbered.

1096
01:04:14,259 --> 01:04:15,540
I need...

1097
01:04:18,740 --> 01:04:20,539
Just be sure.

1098
01:04:21,379 --> 01:04:22,860
Yes, ma'am.

1099
01:04:32,100 --> 01:04:33,939
I can feel the difference.

1100
01:04:41,099 --> 01:04:42,939
(SPEAKING KOREAN)

1101
01:04:46,899 --> 01:04:49,579
Scream, and your entire staff dies.

1102
01:04:49,699 --> 01:04:50,739
(GASPS)

1103
01:04:51,500 --> 01:04:53,739
I could've killed you, Helen,
the night we met.

1104
01:04:53,939 --> 01:04:54,980
I didn't.

1105
01:04:55,100 --> 01:04:56,579
Do you expect a thank-you note?

1106
01:04:56,739 --> 01:04:58,420
I expect you to know why.

1107
01:04:59,899 --> 01:05:01,139
The Cradle.

1108
01:05:01,219 --> 01:05:03,219
DR. CHO ON RECORDING:
<i>This is the next thing, Tony.</i>

1109
01:05:03,299 --> 01:05:06,259
This is the next me.

1110
01:05:06,699 --> 01:05:09,219
The Regeneration Cradle prints tissue.

1111
01:05:09,339 --> 01:05:10,979
It can't build a living body.

1112
01:05:11,100 --> 01:05:12,179
It can. You can.

1113
01:05:12,659 --> 01:05:13,939
You lack the materials.

1114
01:05:16,419 --> 01:05:17,740
You're a brilliant woman, Helen.

1115
01:05:21,020 --> 01:05:24,099
But we all have room to improve.

1116
01:05:45,899 --> 01:05:48,299
I didn't realize you were waiting.

1117
01:05:48,419 --> 01:05:52,819
I would've joined you, but, uh,
it didn't seem like the right time.

1118
01:05:53,779 --> 01:05:55,859
They used up all the hot water.

1119
01:05:56,698 --> 01:05:58,139
I should've joined you.

1120
01:05:58,339 --> 01:05:59,938
Missed our window. (CHUCKLES)

1121
01:06:00,739 --> 01:06:01,979
Did we?

1122
01:06:05,539 --> 01:06:06,658
The world just saw the Hulk.

1123
01:06:09,338 --> 01:06:11,259
The real Hulk, for the first time.

1124
01:06:14,499 --> 01:06:17,139
- You know I have to leave.
- You assume that I have to stay?

1125
01:06:19,218 --> 01:06:21,899
I had this, um, dream.

1126
01:06:22,218 --> 01:06:24,179
The kind that seems normal at the time,

1127
01:06:25,418 --> 01:06:26,659
but when you wake...

1128
01:06:26,859 --> 01:06:28,179
What did you dream?

1129
01:06:29,218 --> 01:06:31,019
That I was an Avenger.

1130
01:06:33,059 --> 01:06:34,339
That I was anything more

1131
01:06:34,499 --> 01:06:36,859
than the assassin they made me.

1132
01:06:38,338 --> 01:06:40,459
I think you're being hard on yourself.

1133
01:06:42,538 --> 01:06:45,018
Here I was hoping that was your job.

1134
01:06:47,978 --> 01:06:49,539
What are you doing?

1135
01:06:51,218 --> 01:06:52,979
I'm running with it.

1136
01:06:54,298 --> 01:06:55,898
With you.

1137
01:06:56,659 --> 01:06:59,018
If running is the plan,

1138
01:07:00,099 --> 01:07:01,858
as far as you want.

1139
01:07:03,779 --> 01:07:05,498
Are you out of your mind?

1140
01:07:10,858 --> 01:07:12,298
I want you to understand that, um...

1141
01:07:12,378 --> 01:07:13,778
Natasha,

1142
01:07:14,898 --> 01:07:16,339
where can I go?

1143
01:07:17,458 --> 01:07:19,739
Where in the world am I not a threat?

1144
01:07:19,859 --> 01:07:22,178
- You're not a threat to me.
- Are you sure?

1145
01:07:23,099 --> 01:07:24,898
Even if I didn't just...

1146
01:07:26,538 --> 01:07:27,898
There's no future with me.

1147
01:07:29,579 --> 01:07:30,578
I can't ever...

1148
01:07:30,818 --> 01:07:33,058
I can't have this.

1149
01:07:33,778 --> 01:07:34,898
Kids.

1150
01:07:35,379 --> 01:07:37,938
Do the math. I physically can't.

1151
01:07:39,698 --> 01:07:41,138
Neither can I.

1152
01:07:45,858 --> 01:07:49,338
In the Red Room where I was trained...

1153
01:07:49,858 --> 01:07:52,298
Where I was raised, um,

1154
01:07:53,258 --> 01:07:55,898
they have a graduation ceremony.

1155
01:07:57,578 --> 01:07:59,338
They sterilize you.

1156
01:08:02,578 --> 01:08:03,978
It's efficient.

1157
01:08:06,898 --> 01:08:08,258
One less thing to worry about.

1158
01:08:10,378 --> 01:08:13,738
The one thing
that might matter more than a mission.

1159
01:08:16,138 --> 01:08:18,018
Makes everything easier.

1160
01:08:19,378 --> 01:08:20,618
Even killing.

1161
01:08:25,698 --> 01:08:28,818
You still think
you're the only monster on the team?

1162
01:08:34,978 --> 01:08:37,057
So, we disappear?

1163
01:08:43,737 --> 01:08:45,578
Thor didn't say
where he was going for answers?

1164
01:08:46,458 --> 01:08:48,938
Sometimes my teammates
don't tell me things.

1165
01:08:50,057 --> 01:08:52,098
I was kind of hoping
Thor would be the exception.

1166
01:08:52,258 --> 01:08:54,258
Yeah, give him time.

1167
01:08:54,378 --> 01:08:56,298
We don't know
what the Maximoff kid showed him.

1168
01:08:58,498 --> 01:09:00,137
"Earth's mightiest heroes."

1169
01:09:00,257 --> 01:09:01,858
Pulled us apart like cotton candy.

1170
01:09:02,218 --> 01:09:03,697
Seems like you walked away all right.

1171
01:09:06,137 --> 01:09:07,137
Is that a problem?

1172
01:09:07,498 --> 01:09:09,417
I don't trust a guy without a dark side.

1173
01:09:10,618 --> 01:09:11,698
Call me old-fashioned.

1174
01:09:11,818 --> 01:09:14,338
Well, let's just say
you haven't seen it yet.

1175
01:09:14,658 --> 01:09:16,857
You know Ultron is trying
to tear us apart, right?

1176
01:09:17,098 --> 01:09:19,337
Well, I guess you'd know.

1177
01:09:19,457 --> 01:09:20,874
Whether you'd tell us
is a bit of a question.

1178
01:09:20,898 --> 01:09:22,153
Banner and I were doing research.

1179
01:09:22,177 --> 01:09:24,378
- That would affect the team.
- That would end the team!

1180
01:09:24,618 --> 01:09:25,697
Isn't that the mission?

1181
01:09:25,897 --> 01:09:27,138
Isn't that the "Why We Fight"?

1182
01:09:27,258 --> 01:09:29,497
So we can end the fight.
So we get to go home!

1183
01:09:32,737 --> 01:09:35,137
Every time someone tries
to win a war before it starts,

1184
01:09:35,257 --> 01:09:36,778
innocent people die.

1185
01:09:36,898 --> 01:09:37,898
Every time.

1186
01:09:40,378 --> 01:09:42,777
I'm sorry. Mr. Stark...

1187
01:09:43,658 --> 01:09:44,817
Clint said you wouldn't mind,

1188
01:09:44,897 --> 01:09:47,378
but our tractor doesn't seem
to want to start at all.

1189
01:09:47,698 --> 01:09:50,058
- I thought maybe you might...
- Yeah, I'll give her a kick.

1190
01:09:53,498 --> 01:09:55,057
Don't take from my pile.

1191
01:09:56,217 --> 01:09:57,218
(DOOR OPENS)

1192
01:10:05,297 --> 01:10:06,498
Hello, Deere.

1193
01:10:09,377 --> 01:10:10,737
Tell me everything.

1194
01:10:11,977 --> 01:10:13,378
What ails you?

1195
01:10:13,577 --> 01:10:14,577
FURY: Do me a favor.

1196
01:10:16,857 --> 01:10:18,737
Try not to bring it to life.

1197
01:10:18,897 --> 01:10:20,417
Why, Ms. Barton, you little minx.

1198
01:10:20,777 --> 01:10:23,297
I get it. Maria Hill called you, right?

1199
01:10:23,417 --> 01:10:24,737
Was she ever not working for you?

1200
01:10:24,817 --> 01:10:26,297
Artificial intelligence.

1201
01:10:27,337 --> 01:10:29,017
You never even hesitated.

1202
01:10:29,298 --> 01:10:30,657
Look, it's been a really long day,

1203
01:10:30,737 --> 01:10:32,337
like Eugene O'Neill long,

1204
01:10:32,458 --> 01:10:34,617
so how's about
we skip to the part where you're useful.

1205
01:10:34,657 --> 01:10:35,898
Look me in the eye and tell me

1206
01:10:36,017 --> 01:10:37,257
you're going to shut him down.

1207
01:10:37,577 --> 01:10:38,977
You're not the director of me.

1208
01:10:39,098 --> 01:10:40,937
I'm not the director of anybody.

1209
01:10:41,257 --> 01:10:42,857
I'm just an old man

1210
01:10:43,537 --> 01:10:45,097
who cares very much about you.

1211
01:10:47,977 --> 01:10:49,777
And I'm the man
who killed the Avengers.

1212
01:10:51,617 --> 01:10:52,737
I saw it.

1213
01:10:52,937 --> 01:10:54,497
I didn't tell the team. How could I?

1214
01:10:55,777 --> 01:10:57,617
I saw them all dead, Nick. I felt it.

1215
01:10:57,977 --> 01:10:59,497
The whole world, too.

1216
01:10:59,937 --> 01:11:00,937
Because of me.

1217
01:11:02,217 --> 01:11:03,617
I wasn't ready.

1218
01:11:05,136 --> 01:11:06,497
I didn't do all I could.

1219
01:11:07,537 --> 01:11:09,617
Maximoff girl, she's working you, Stark.

1220
01:11:10,257 --> 01:11:13,777
- Playing on your fear.
- I wasn't tricked, I was shown.

1221
01:11:13,897 --> 01:11:16,137
Wasn't a nightmare, it was my legacy.

1222
01:11:16,457 --> 01:11:18,657
The end of the path I started us on.

1223
01:11:19,497 --> 01:11:21,737
You come up with some pretty
impressive inventions, Tony.

1224
01:11:23,897 --> 01:11:25,297
War isn't one of them.

1225
01:11:28,897 --> 01:11:30,337
I watched my friends die.

1226
01:11:30,616 --> 01:11:32,617
You'd think that'd be
as bad as it gets, right?

1227
01:11:32,737 --> 01:11:33,816
(SCOFFS)

1228
01:11:34,056 --> 01:11:35,497
Nope.

1229
01:11:36,497 --> 01:11:39,017
- It wasn't the worst part.
- The worst part

1230
01:11:40,057 --> 01:11:41,337
is that you didn't.

1231
01:11:48,097 --> 01:11:49,257
SELVIG: I'll see you tonight.

1232
01:11:51,937 --> 01:11:53,176
I like the look.

1233
01:11:54,336 --> 01:11:56,896
If you're going for inconspicuous,
though, near miss.

1234
01:11:57,216 --> 01:11:58,257
I need your help.

1235
01:11:58,497 --> 01:11:59,496
It's nice to be needed.

1236
01:11:59,896 --> 01:12:01,257
It's dangerous.

1237
01:12:01,897 --> 01:12:03,656
I'd be disappointed if it wasn't.

1238
01:12:06,576 --> 01:12:09,856
FURY: Ultron took you folks out of play
to buy himself time.

1239
01:12:10,216 --> 01:12:13,176
My contacts all say
he's building something.

1240
01:12:13,296 --> 01:12:15,896
The amount of vibranium
he made off with,

1241
01:12:16,016 --> 01:12:17,497
I don't think it's just one thing.

1242
01:12:17,617 --> 01:12:18,936
What about Ultron himself?

1243
01:12:19,056 --> 01:12:21,417
FURY: Oh, he's easy to track.
He's everywhere.

1244
01:12:21,857 --> 01:12:24,257
The guy is multiplying faster
than a Catholic rabbit.

1245
01:12:24,897 --> 01:12:27,697
It still doesn't help us get an angle
on any of his plans, though.

1246
01:12:27,937 --> 01:12:29,272
Is he still going after launch codes?

1247
01:12:29,296 --> 01:12:30,657
FURY: Yes, he is.

1248
01:12:30,777 --> 01:12:32,256
But he's not making any headway.

1249
01:12:32,376 --> 01:12:34,553
I cracked the Pentagon's firewall
in high school on a dare.

1250
01:12:34,577 --> 01:12:37,177
Well, I contacted our friends
at the Nexus about that.

1251
01:12:37,257 --> 01:12:38,256
Nexus?

1252
01:12:38,376 --> 01:12:40,096
BANNER: It's the world
Internet hub in Oslo.

1253
01:12:40,457 --> 01:12:42,216
Every byte of data flows through there.

1254
01:12:42,456 --> 01:12:43,496
Fastest access on Earth.

1255
01:12:43,697 --> 01:12:44,736
So, what did they say?

1256
01:12:44,936 --> 01:12:46,736
FURY: He's fixated on the missiles.

1257
01:12:46,937 --> 01:12:48,616
But the codes
are constantly being changed.

1258
01:12:49,096 --> 01:12:50,096
By whom?

1259
01:12:51,336 --> 01:12:52,576
Parties unknown.

1260
01:12:52,736 --> 01:12:53,857
Do we have an ally?

1261
01:12:53,977 --> 01:12:56,336
Ultron's got an enemy.
That's not the same thing.

1262
01:12:56,656 --> 01:12:58,496
Still, I'd pay folding money
to know who it is.

1263
01:12:58,616 --> 01:12:59,776
I might need to visit Oslo.

1264
01:13:00,297 --> 01:13:01,416
Find our unknown.

1265
01:13:01,576 --> 01:13:03,016
Well, this is good times, boss,

1266
01:13:03,136 --> 01:13:04,512
but I was kind of hoping when I saw you,

1267
01:13:04,536 --> 01:13:05,576
you'd have more than that.

1268
01:13:05,816 --> 01:13:07,816
I do. I have you.

1269
01:13:08,696 --> 01:13:10,456
Back in the day, I had eyes everywhere.

1270
01:13:10,616 --> 01:13:11,936
Ears, everywhere else.

1271
01:13:12,256 --> 01:13:15,256
You kids had all the tech
you could dream up.

1272
01:13:16,256 --> 01:13:18,256
Here we all are, back on Earth,

1273
01:13:18,496 --> 01:13:20,256
with nothing but our wit

1274
01:13:20,416 --> 01:13:21,976
and our will to save the world.

1275
01:13:23,576 --> 01:13:25,776
Ultron says the Avengers
are the only thing

1276
01:13:25,936 --> 01:13:27,376
between him and his mission.

1277
01:13:27,496 --> 01:13:29,696
And whether or not he admits it,

1278
01:13:29,816 --> 01:13:32,575
his mission is global destruction.

1279
01:13:33,776 --> 01:13:35,935
All this, laid in a grave.

1280
01:13:37,976 --> 01:13:39,656
So stand.

1281
01:13:40,456 --> 01:13:42,176
Outwit the platinum bastard.

1282
01:13:42,816 --> 01:13:44,296
Steve doesn't like that kind of talk.

1283
01:13:44,496 --> 01:13:45,575
You know what, Romanoff?

1284
01:13:46,776 --> 01:13:48,096
So, what does he want?

1285
01:13:49,816 --> 01:13:51,536
To become better.

1286
01:13:51,656 --> 01:13:53,056
Better than us.

1287
01:13:53,376 --> 01:13:55,776
- He keeps building bodies.
- Person bodies.

1288
01:13:56,376 --> 01:13:58,016
The human form is inefficient.

1289
01:13:58,136 --> 01:14:00,296
Biologically speaking, we're outmoded.

1290
01:14:00,416 --> 01:14:02,376
But he keeps coming back to it.

1291
01:14:02,496 --> 01:14:04,616
When you two programmed him
to protect the human race,

1292
01:14:04,656 --> 01:14:05,976
you amazingly failed.

1293
01:14:06,296 --> 01:14:08,135
They don't need to be protected.

1294
01:14:08,856 --> 01:14:10,336
They need to evolve.

1295
01:14:12,496 --> 01:14:14,495
Ultron's going to evolve.

1296
01:14:14,655 --> 01:14:15,696
How?

1297
01:14:17,016 --> 01:14:19,696
Has anyone been in contact
with Helen Cho?

1298
01:14:23,456 --> 01:14:25,095
DR. CHO: It's beautiful.

1299
01:14:25,536 --> 01:14:28,455
The vibranium atoms aren't just
compatible with the tissue cells,

1300
01:14:28,576 --> 01:14:29,816
they're binding them.

1301
01:14:30,296 --> 01:14:31,791
And S.H.I.E.L.D.
never even thought to...

1302
01:14:31,816 --> 01:14:34,375
The most versatile substance
on the planet,

1303
01:14:34,495 --> 01:14:37,015
and they used it to make a Frisbee.

1304
01:14:37,175 --> 01:14:38,295
Typical of humans.

1305
01:14:38,496 --> 01:14:41,015
They scratch the surface
and never think

1306
01:14:42,976 --> 01:14:44,495
to look within.

1307
01:14:55,016 --> 01:14:56,495
I'll take Natasha and Clint.

1308
01:14:56,695 --> 01:14:58,656
All right. Strictly
recon. I'll hit the Nexus.

1309
01:14:58,776 --> 01:14:59,991
I'll join you as soon as I can.

1310
01:15:00,015 --> 01:15:01,536
If Ultron's really building a body...

1311
01:15:01,776 --> 01:15:03,295
He'll be more powerful than any of us.

1312
01:15:03,495 --> 01:15:04,575
Maybe all of us.

1313
01:15:05,096 --> 01:15:06,895
An android designed by a robot.

1314
01:15:07,135 --> 01:15:08,392
You know, I really miss the days

1315
01:15:08,416 --> 01:15:10,535
when the weirdest thing
science ever created was me.

1316
01:15:11,176 --> 01:15:12,775
I'll drop Banner off at the tower.

1317
01:15:12,935 --> 01:15:14,215
You mind if I borrow Ms. Hill?

1318
01:15:14,456 --> 01:15:16,215
She's all yours. Apparently.

1319
01:15:16,375 --> 01:15:17,535
What are you gonna do?

1320
01:15:17,695 --> 01:15:20,775
I don't know.
Something dramatic, I hope.

1321
01:15:24,135 --> 01:15:25,895
I'm gonna finish reflooring that sunroom

1322
01:15:26,055 --> 01:15:27,856
as soon as I get back.

1323
01:15:28,056 --> 01:15:30,735
Yeah, then you'll find
another part of the house to tear apart.

1324
01:15:30,896 --> 01:15:32,055
No.

1325
01:15:32,735 --> 01:15:34,216
It's the last project.

1326
01:15:35,735 --> 01:15:36,735
I promise.

1327
01:15:55,055 --> 01:15:56,535
SELVIG: So, this is it.

1328
01:15:58,175 --> 01:16:00,415
The Water of Sight.

1329
01:16:02,735 --> 01:16:05,135
THOR: In every realm,
there's a reflection.

1330
01:16:06,335 --> 01:16:07,655
If the water's spirits accept me,

1331
01:16:07,855 --> 01:16:09,815
I can return to my dream

1332
01:16:10,575 --> 01:16:12,015
and find what I missed.

1333
01:16:12,255 --> 01:16:16,095
Men who enter that water,
the legends don't end well.

1334
01:16:17,775 --> 01:16:19,535
STARK: A hacker
who's faster than Ultron?

1335
01:16:19,694 --> 01:16:20,735
He could be anywhere,

1336
01:16:20,855 --> 01:16:23,094
and as this is the center of everything,

1337
01:16:23,214 --> 01:16:24,511
I'm just a guy looking for a needle

1338
01:16:24,535 --> 01:16:26,615
in the world's biggest haystack.

1339
01:16:27,615 --> 01:16:29,214
How do you find it?

1340
01:16:29,614 --> 01:16:32,215
It's pretty simple. You bring a magnet.

1341
01:16:34,375 --> 01:16:35,591
(SINGING) <i>I'm decrypting nuclear codes</i>

1342
01:16:35,615 --> 01:16:36,935
<i>And you don't want me to</i>

1343
01:16:39,254 --> 01:16:40,735
Come and get me.

1344
01:16:42,294 --> 01:16:43,615
(PANTING)

1345
01:16:53,095 --> 01:16:54,135
Wake up!

1346
01:16:54,455 --> 01:16:55,654
(GROANING)

1347
01:17:00,975 --> 01:17:01,974
Thor!

1348
01:17:02,815 --> 01:17:03,855
Extinction.

1349
01:17:13,655 --> 01:17:14,894
(SCREAMS)

1350
01:17:17,335 --> 01:17:19,455
DR. CHO: Cellular cohesion
will take a few hours,

1351
01:17:19,655 --> 01:17:22,094
but we can initiate
the consciousness stream.

1352
01:17:22,655 --> 01:17:25,454
We're uploading your cerebral matrix

1353
01:17:25,655 --> 01:17:26,895
now.

1354
01:17:27,015 --> 01:17:28,214
(BEEPING)

1355
01:17:28,334 --> 01:17:29,935
I can read him.

1356
01:17:30,654 --> 01:17:32,175
He's dreaming.

1357
01:17:32,415 --> 01:17:34,214
DR. CHO: I wouldn't call it dreams.

1358
01:17:34,454 --> 01:17:36,295
It's Ultron's base consciousness.

1359
01:17:36,495 --> 01:17:38,014
Informational noise. Soon...

1360
01:17:38,254 --> 01:17:39,375
How soon?

1361
01:17:39,655 --> 01:17:40,934
I'm not being pushy.

1362
01:17:41,174 --> 01:17:42,855
DR. CHO: We're imprinting
a physical brain.

1363
01:17:42,975 --> 01:17:44,414
There are no shortcuts.

1364
01:17:44,694 --> 01:17:45,895
Even if your magic gem...

1365
01:17:47,854 --> 01:17:49,375
(SCREAMS)

1366
01:17:49,534 --> 01:17:51,134
(WANDA PANTING)

1367
01:17:56,614 --> 01:17:57,974
How could you?

1368
01:17:58,014 --> 01:17:59,055
How could I what?

1369
01:17:59,334 --> 01:18:02,494
You said we would
destroy the Avengers,

1370
01:18:02,654 --> 01:18:03,694
make a better world.

1371
01:18:04,054 --> 01:18:05,095
It will be better.

1372
01:18:06,054 --> 01:18:08,375
- When everyone is dead?
- That is not...

1373
01:18:09,334 --> 01:18:13,174
The human race will have
every opportunity to improve.

1374
01:18:13,694 --> 01:18:15,015
And if they don't?

1375
01:18:15,214 --> 01:18:16,334
Ask Noah.

1376
01:18:17,534 --> 01:18:18,574
You are a madman.

1377
01:18:18,734 --> 01:18:22,134
There were more than a dozen
extinction-level events

1378
01:18:22,294 --> 01:18:25,374
before even the dinosaurs got theirs.

1379
01:18:25,534 --> 01:18:27,654
When the Earth starts to settle,

1380
01:18:28,174 --> 01:18:30,054
God throws a stone at it.

1381
01:18:30,214 --> 01:18:32,534
And, believe me, he's winding up.

1382
01:18:33,334 --> 01:18:34,494
We have to evolve.

1383
01:18:35,054 --> 01:18:36,254
There's no room

1384
01:18:37,054 --> 01:18:38,214
for the weak.

1385
01:18:38,414 --> 01:18:40,374
PIETRO: And who decides who's weak?

1386
01:18:41,254 --> 01:18:42,974
Life. (CHUCKLES)

1387
01:18:43,614 --> 01:18:45,414
Life always decides.

1388
01:18:45,494 --> 01:18:46,614
(AIRCRAFT APPROACHING)

1389
01:18:48,374 --> 01:18:49,414
There's incoming.

1390
01:18:50,934 --> 01:18:54,214
- The Quinjet. We have to move.
- That's not a problem.

1391
01:18:57,614 --> 01:18:59,214
- (SIGHS IN ANNOYANCE)
- (DR. CHO GROANS)

1392
01:19:01,214 --> 01:19:02,214
(STAMMERS) Wait, guys!

1393
01:19:03,214 --> 01:19:04,214
(BOTH GROANING)

1394
01:19:06,254 --> 01:19:07,574
They'll understand.

1395
01:19:07,854 --> 01:19:09,973
When they see, they'll understand.

1396
01:19:10,413 --> 01:19:13,653
I just need a little more time.

1397
01:19:25,094 --> 01:19:27,174
Two minutes. Stay close.

1398
01:19:34,374 --> 01:19:35,374
Dr. Cho!

1399
01:19:35,933 --> 01:19:37,254
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1400
01:19:39,293 --> 01:19:40,814
He's uploading himself into the body.

1401
01:19:40,934 --> 01:19:41,973
Where?

1402
01:19:43,774 --> 01:19:46,333
The real power is inside the Cradle.

1403
01:19:46,413 --> 01:19:47,454
The gem,

1404
01:19:48,214 --> 01:19:50,934
its power is uncontainable.

1405
01:19:51,813 --> 01:19:53,494
You can't just blow it up.

1406
01:19:54,454 --> 01:19:56,654
You have to get the Cradle to Stark.

1407
01:19:56,774 --> 01:19:57,814
First, I have to find it.

1408
01:19:58,173 --> 01:19:59,173
Go.

1409
01:19:59,493 --> 01:20:00,734
ROGERS: <i>Did you guys copy that?</i>

1410
01:20:00,894 --> 01:20:01,973
We did.

1411
01:20:02,173 --> 01:20:04,573
I got a private jet taking off across town.

1412
01:20:04,933 --> 01:20:06,213
No manifest.

1413
01:20:06,334 --> 01:20:07,374
That could be him.

1414
01:20:08,333 --> 01:20:09,934
There. It's a truck from the lab.

1415
01:20:10,094 --> 01:20:11,253
Right above you, Cap.

1416
01:20:11,533 --> 01:20:13,334
On the loop by the bridge.

1417
01:20:13,974 --> 01:20:14,973
It's them.

1418
01:20:15,093 --> 01:20:16,894
You got three with the Cradle,
one in the cab.

1419
01:20:17,653 --> 01:20:18,773
I could take out the driver.

1420
01:20:18,853 --> 01:20:19,990
ROGERS: <i>Negative. That truck crashes,</i>

1421
01:20:20,014 --> 01:20:21,613
the gem could level the city.

1422
01:20:22,013 --> 01:20:23,254
<i>We need to draw out Ultron.</i>

1423
01:20:25,853 --> 01:20:26,893
(PANTING)

1424
01:20:31,293 --> 01:20:32,293
(GRUNTS)

1425
01:20:32,974 --> 01:20:35,013
No, no, no, no.

1426
01:20:36,853 --> 01:20:37,893
Leave me alone!

1427
01:20:39,214 --> 01:20:40,373
(GROANS)

1428
01:20:46,533 --> 01:20:48,213
Well, he's definitely unhappy.

1429
01:20:48,373 --> 01:20:49,853
I'm gonna try and keep him that way.

1430
01:20:50,013 --> 01:20:51,149
You're not a match for him, Cap.

1431
01:20:51,173 --> 01:20:52,254
(PANTING)

1432
01:20:52,374 --> 01:20:53,453
Thanks, Barton.

1433
01:21:03,333 --> 01:21:04,333
(GASPS)

1434
01:21:04,853 --> 01:21:06,493
(PEOPLE CHATTERING EXCITEDLY)

1435
01:21:16,173 --> 01:21:17,413
You know what's in that cradle?

1436
01:21:18,733 --> 01:21:20,453
The power to make real change.

1437
01:21:20,573 --> 01:21:21,973
And that terrifies you.

1438
01:21:22,173 --> 01:21:23,333
I wouldn't call it a comfort.

1439
01:21:26,533 --> 01:21:27,573
Stop it.

1440
01:21:38,413 --> 01:21:41,092
We got a window. Four, three...

1441
01:21:41,773 --> 01:21:42,773
Give him hell.

1442
01:21:53,692 --> 01:21:55,173
I'm always picking up after you boys.

1443
01:21:56,773 --> 01:21:58,749
They're heading under the overpass.
I've got no shot.

1444
01:21:58,773 --> 01:21:59,813
ROMANOFF: <i>Which way?</i>

1445
01:22:00,013 --> 01:22:01,012
Hard right.

1446
01:22:02,173 --> 01:22:03,292
Now.

1447
01:22:04,292 --> 01:22:05,293
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

1448
01:22:17,733 --> 01:22:19,013
(TIRES SQUEALING)

1449
01:22:21,293 --> 01:22:22,293
(GRUNTING)

1450
01:22:28,093 --> 01:22:29,732
(ENGINE REVVING)

1451
01:22:34,133 --> 01:22:36,412
Out of the way! Coming through!
Sorry, coming through!

1452
01:22:52,212 --> 01:22:53,332
Come on!

1453
01:22:53,813 --> 01:22:55,348
ROMANOFF: Clint,
can you draw out the guards?

1454
01:22:55,372 --> 01:22:56,412
Let's find out.

1455
01:22:57,453 --> 01:22:58,492
ROMANOFF: Beep, beep!

1456
01:23:17,612 --> 01:23:19,452
(SPEAKING KOREAN)

1457
01:23:32,732 --> 01:23:33,812
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1458
01:23:36,012 --> 01:23:37,532
They're heading back towards you.

1459
01:23:37,692 --> 01:23:39,252
So whatever you're gonna do, do it now.

1460
01:23:44,732 --> 01:23:47,372
ROMANOFF: <i>I'm going in.
Cap, can you keep him occupied?</i>

1461
01:23:47,532 --> 01:23:49,412
(PANTING)
What do you think I've been doing?

1462
01:24:20,572 --> 01:24:21,691
(YELPING)

1463
01:24:30,492 --> 01:24:31,892
(STRAINING)

1464
01:24:33,012 --> 01:24:35,131
BARTON: <i>Okay, package is airborne.</i>

1465
01:24:35,852 --> 01:24:36,932
I have a clean shot.

1466
01:24:37,372 --> 01:24:38,732
Negative. I am still in the truck.

1467
01:24:38,892 --> 01:24:40,028
- What the hell are you...
- Just be ready.

1468
01:24:40,052 --> 01:24:41,291
I'm sending the package to you.

1469
01:24:41,772 --> 01:24:42,972
How do you want me to take it?

1470
01:24:43,172 --> 01:24:45,292
Uh, you might wish
you hadn't asked that.

1471
01:24:58,091 --> 01:24:59,772
Please, don't do this.

1472
01:25:00,291 --> 01:25:01,852
What choice do we have?

1473
01:25:10,131 --> 01:25:11,131
I lost him!

1474
01:25:11,292 --> 01:25:12,652
He's headed your way!

1475
01:25:12,811 --> 01:25:13,931
(ALARM BLARING)

1476
01:25:17,651 --> 01:25:18,692
Nat, we gotta go.

1477
01:25:29,971 --> 01:25:31,772
- (GROANS)
- Nat!

1478
01:25:35,811 --> 01:25:36,811
Cap, you see Nat?

1479
01:25:37,772 --> 01:25:40,331
If you have the package,
get it to Stark! Go!

1480
01:25:40,651 --> 01:25:41,811
Do you have eyes on Nat?

1481
01:25:42,011 --> 01:25:43,011
<i>Go!</i>

1482
01:25:45,011 --> 01:25:46,011
Damn it.

1483
01:25:46,491 --> 01:25:47,572
Civilians in our path.

1484
01:25:48,891 --> 01:25:50,371
Can you stop this thing?

1485
01:25:51,971 --> 01:25:53,131
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1486
01:26:00,251 --> 01:26:01,331
(GRUNTS)

1487
01:26:18,851 --> 01:26:20,411
(PANTING)

1488
01:26:29,251 --> 01:26:30,571
I'm fine.

1489
01:26:30,691 --> 01:26:32,371
I just need to take a minute.

1490
01:26:32,891 --> 01:26:34,771
I'm very tempted not to give you one.

1491
01:26:34,891 --> 01:26:36,811
The Cradle. Did you get it?

1492
01:26:36,971 --> 01:26:38,451
Stark will take care of it.

1493
01:26:39,851 --> 01:26:40,851
No, he won't.

1494
01:26:44,371 --> 01:26:45,667
You don't know
what you're talking about.

1495
01:26:45,691 --> 01:26:46,691
Stark's not crazy.

1496
01:26:46,731 --> 01:26:48,851
He will do anything to make things right.

1497
01:26:53,731 --> 01:26:55,011
Stark, come in.

1498
01:26:55,530 --> 01:26:56,571
Stark.

1499
01:26:57,891 --> 01:26:59,010
Anyone on comms.

1500
01:26:59,170 --> 01:27:00,571
Ultron can't tell the difference

1501
01:27:00,731 --> 01:27:03,091
between saving the world
and destroying it.

1502
01:27:04,971 --> 01:27:07,411
Where do you think he gets that?

1503
01:27:09,611 --> 01:27:11,171
- Anything on Nat?
- I haven't heard.

1504
01:27:11,291 --> 01:27:13,651
But she's alive, or Ultron would
be rubbing our faces in it.

1505
01:27:13,811 --> 01:27:15,090
This is sealed tight.

1506
01:27:15,250 --> 01:27:16,771
We're gonna need
to access the program,

1507
01:27:16,851 --> 01:27:18,770
break it down from within.

1508
01:27:19,971 --> 01:27:21,330
Any chance Natasha might leave you

1509
01:27:21,410 --> 01:27:22,771
a message outside the Internet?

1510
01:27:22,811 --> 01:27:23,851
Old-school spy stuff?

1511
01:27:24,331 --> 01:27:26,131
BARTON: There are
some nets I can cast.

1512
01:27:26,251 --> 01:27:27,531
Yeah, I'll find her.

1513
01:27:30,091 --> 01:27:31,850
I can work on tissue degeneration

1514
01:27:31,970 --> 01:27:35,210
if you could fry whatever
operational system Cho implanted.

1515
01:27:35,370 --> 01:27:36,451
Yeah, about that.

1516
01:27:40,890 --> 01:27:41,890
No.

1517
01:27:42,131 --> 01:27:43,930
- You have to trust me.
- Kind of don't.

1518
01:27:44,130 --> 01:27:48,130
Our ally, the guy protecting
the military's nuclear codes,

1519
01:27:50,091 --> 01:27:51,130
I found him.

1520
01:27:51,170 --> 01:27:52,291
JARVIS: <i>Hello, Dr. Banner.</i>

1521
01:27:53,171 --> 01:27:55,452
STARK: Ultron didn't go after Jarvis
because he was angry.

1522
01:27:56,011 --> 01:27:59,611
He attacked him because he was
scared of what he can do.

1523
01:28:00,810 --> 01:28:02,411
So Jarvis went underground.

1524
01:28:02,571 --> 01:28:04,010
Scattered, dumped his memory.

1525
01:28:04,650 --> 01:28:06,091
But not his protocols.

1526
01:28:06,570 --> 01:28:09,970
He didn't even know he was in there
until I pieced him together.

1527
01:28:10,130 --> 01:28:11,130
(BANNER SCOFFS)

1528
01:28:12,810 --> 01:28:17,610
So, you want me to help you
put Jarvis into this thing?

1529
01:28:17,730 --> 01:28:19,490
No! Of course not.

1530
01:28:19,650 --> 01:28:21,330
I wanna help you put Jarvis in this thing.

1531
01:28:23,730 --> 01:28:25,371
We're out of my field, here.

1532
01:28:25,490 --> 01:28:27,490
You know bio-organics
better than anyone.

1533
01:28:27,810 --> 01:28:30,690
And you just assume
that Jarvis's operational matrix

1534
01:28:30,810 --> 01:28:32,250
can beat Ultron's?

1535
01:28:32,370 --> 01:28:35,650
Jarvis has been beating him
from inside without knowing it.

1536
01:28:35,850 --> 01:28:36,850
This is the opportunity.

1537
01:28:36,930 --> 01:28:38,650
We can create Ultron's perfect self

1538
01:28:38,850 --> 01:28:42,290
without the homicidal glitches
he thinks are his winning personality.

1539
01:28:42,410 --> 01:28:44,491
- We have to.
<i>- I believe it's worth a go.</i>

1540
01:28:47,090 --> 01:28:48,170
I'm in a loop!

1541
01:28:48,330 --> 01:28:51,290
I'm caught in a time loop.
This is exactly where it all went wrong.

1542
01:28:51,450 --> 01:28:53,370
I know. I know. I know
what everyone's gonna say.

1543
01:28:53,450 --> 01:28:55,410
But they're already saying it.

1544
01:28:55,930 --> 01:28:57,090
We're mad scientists.

1545
01:28:57,850 --> 01:29:00,570
We're monsters, buddy.
We've gotta own it.

1546
01:29:01,570 --> 01:29:02,810
Make a stand.

1547
01:29:08,210 --> 01:29:09,690
It's not a loop.

1548
01:29:10,970 --> 01:29:12,690
It's the end of the line.

1549
01:29:33,209 --> 01:29:35,370
I wasn't sure you would wake up.

1550
01:29:35,490 --> 01:29:38,890
I hoped you would.
I wanted to show you.

1551
01:29:39,050 --> 01:29:40,730
I don't have anyone else.

1552
01:29:40,890 --> 01:29:42,170
(GROANING)

1553
01:29:43,570 --> 01:29:47,210
I think a lot about meteors.
The purity in them.

1554
01:29:47,330 --> 01:29:48,850
Boom! The end.

1555
01:29:49,329 --> 01:29:50,730
Start again.

1556
01:29:50,890 --> 01:29:52,849
The world made clean

1557
01:29:53,009 --> 01:29:55,290
for the new man to rebuild.

1558
01:29:55,609 --> 01:29:57,730
I was meant to be new.

1559
01:29:58,609 --> 01:30:01,210
I was meant to be beautiful.

1560
01:30:01,810 --> 01:30:03,890
The world would have looked to the sky

1561
01:30:04,010 --> 01:30:05,249
and seen hope,

1562
01:30:05,609 --> 01:30:06,930
seen mercy.

1563
01:30:07,770 --> 01:30:09,810
Instead, they'll look up in horror

1564
01:30:09,930 --> 01:30:11,250
because of you.

1565
01:30:11,450 --> 01:30:13,250
You've wounded me.

1566
01:30:13,930 --> 01:30:15,609
I give you full marks for that.

1567
01:30:16,250 --> 01:30:19,169
But, like the man said,
what doesn't kill me...

1568
01:30:20,610 --> 01:30:21,769
(GASPS)

1569
01:30:24,409 --> 01:30:25,729
just makes me stronger.

1570
01:30:25,849 --> 01:30:26,930
(PANTING)

1571
01:30:47,769 --> 01:30:49,650
(STATIC)

1572
01:31:01,649 --> 01:31:02,650
(TYPING)

1573
01:31:05,810 --> 01:31:07,969
This framework is not compatible.

1574
01:31:08,169 --> 01:31:10,809
The genetic coding tower is at 97%.

1575
01:31:10,929 --> 01:31:14,769
You have got to upload that schematic
in the next three minutes.

1576
01:31:17,089 --> 01:31:19,009
- I'm gonna say this once.
- How about "none-ce"?

1577
01:31:19,169 --> 01:31:21,209
- ROGERS: Shut it down!
- Nope, not gonna happen.

1578
01:31:21,329 --> 01:31:22,625
You don't know what you're doing.

1579
01:31:22,649 --> 01:31:23,969
And you do?

1580
01:31:24,329 --> 01:31:25,329
She's not in your head?

1581
01:31:25,489 --> 01:31:27,129
I know you're angry.

1582
01:31:27,249 --> 01:31:28,649
Oh, we're way past that.

1583
01:31:28,769 --> 01:31:31,169
I could choke the life out of you
and never change a shade.

1584
01:31:31,409 --> 01:31:33,089
Banner, after everything
that's happened...

1585
01:31:33,169 --> 01:31:34,665
It's nothing compared to what's coming!

1586
01:31:34,689 --> 01:31:37,249
WANDA: You don't know what's in there.
ROGERS: This isn't a game!

1587
01:31:40,329 --> 01:31:41,729
- No, no. Go on.
- (POWERING DOWN)

1588
01:31:42,689 --> 01:31:44,608
- You were saying?
- (GUNSHOT)

1589
01:31:50,849 --> 01:31:51,889
- Pietro!
- (GRUNTS)

1590
01:31:52,449 --> 01:31:53,529
BARTON: What?

1591
01:31:53,929 --> 01:31:55,489
You didn't see that coming?

1592
01:31:57,688 --> 01:31:58,889
I'm rerouting the upload.

1593
01:32:05,169 --> 01:32:06,929
- (GASPS)
- Go ahead, piss me off.

1594
01:32:07,049 --> 01:32:08,249
(GUN COCKS)

1595
01:32:09,249 --> 01:32:10,289
(GRUNTING)

1596
01:32:11,369 --> 01:32:12,369
(GROANS)

1597
01:32:13,528 --> 01:32:14,689
(GROANS)

1598
01:32:19,249 --> 01:32:20,408
Wait!

1599
01:32:36,888 --> 01:32:38,169
(GRUNTING)

1600
01:33:45,048 --> 01:33:47,288
I am sorry. That was

1601
01:33:48,328 --> 01:33:49,689
odd.

1602
01:33:49,928 --> 01:33:51,208
Thank you.

1603
01:33:52,568 --> 01:33:53,608
(SIGHS)

1604
01:33:56,089 --> 01:33:57,168
ROGERS: Thor.

1605
01:33:58,648 --> 01:34:01,248
- You helped create this?
- THOR: I've had a vision.

1606
01:34:01,488 --> 01:34:05,208
A whirlpool that sucks in all hope of life,
and at its center is that.

1607
01:34:06,168 --> 01:34:07,168
What? The gem?

1608
01:34:07,328 --> 01:34:09,928
It's the Mind Stone.
It's one of the six Infinity Stones.

1609
01:34:10,048 --> 01:34:11,384
The greatest power in the universe,

1610
01:34:11,408 --> 01:34:13,568
unparalleled in
its destructive capabilities.

1611
01:34:13,728 --> 01:34:15,824
- Then why would you bring...
- Because Stark is right.

1612
01:34:15,848 --> 01:34:18,288
Oh, it's definitely the end times.

1613
01:34:18,488 --> 01:34:19,784
The Avengers cannot defeat Ultron.

1614
01:34:19,808 --> 01:34:21,048
Not alone.

1615
01:34:21,448 --> 01:34:23,368
Why does your Vision sound like Jarvis?

1616
01:34:23,528 --> 01:34:26,168
We reconfigured Jarvis's matrix

1617
01:34:26,688 --> 01:34:28,487
to create something new.

1618
01:34:28,688 --> 01:34:30,408
ROGERS: I think I've had my fill of new.

1619
01:34:30,528 --> 01:34:32,808
You think I'm a child of Ultron.

1620
01:34:33,208 --> 01:34:34,448
ROGERS: You're not?

1621
01:34:35,608 --> 01:34:37,208
I'm not Ultron.

1622
01:34:37,808 --> 01:34:40,008
I am not Jarvis. I am...

1623
01:34:42,168 --> 01:34:43,528
I am.

1624
01:34:45,448 --> 01:34:46,568
WANDA: I looked in your head

1625
01:34:47,288 --> 01:34:49,048
and saw annihilation.

1626
01:34:49,208 --> 01:34:50,568
- Look again.
- (BARTON SCOFFS)

1627
01:34:50,688 --> 01:34:52,208
Her seal of approval means jack to me.

1628
01:34:52,728 --> 01:34:54,727
Their powers, the horrors in our heads,

1629
01:34:54,887 --> 01:34:56,888
Ultron himself, they all came
from the Mind Stone.

1630
01:34:57,048 --> 01:34:59,208
And they're nothing
compared to what it can unleash.

1631
01:34:59,368 --> 01:35:01,127
- But with it on our side...
- ROGERS: Is it?

1632
01:35:02,328 --> 01:35:03,528
Are you?

1633
01:35:04,367 --> 01:35:05,808
On our side?

1634
01:35:07,687 --> 01:35:09,568
I don't think it's that simple.

1635
01:35:09,728 --> 01:35:12,168
BARTON: Well, it better
get real simple real soon.

1636
01:35:13,368 --> 01:35:15,448
I am on the side of life.

1637
01:35:15,688 --> 01:35:17,047
Ultron isn't.

1638
01:35:17,647 --> 01:35:19,048
He will end it all.

1639
01:35:19,248 --> 01:35:21,168
STARK: What's he waiting for?

1640
01:35:21,288 --> 01:35:22,288
- You.
- BANNER: Where?

1641
01:35:22,728 --> 01:35:23,887
BARTON: Sokovia.

1642
01:35:24,047 --> 01:35:25,128
He's got Nat there, too.

1643
01:35:27,247 --> 01:35:28,928
If we're wrong about you,

1644
01:35:31,568 --> 01:35:33,567
if you're the monster
that Ultron made you to be...

1645
01:35:34,087 --> 01:35:35,608
What will you do?

1646
01:35:42,248 --> 01:35:44,328
I don't want to kill Ultron.

1647
01:35:44,728 --> 01:35:48,048
He's unique and he's in pain.

1648
01:35:49,607 --> 01:35:52,167
But that pain will roll over the Earth.

1649
01:35:52,727 --> 01:35:55,008
So, he must be destroyed.

1650
01:35:55,287 --> 01:35:58,168
Every form he's built,
every trace of his presence on the net.

1651
01:35:58,447 --> 01:36:00,087
We have to act now.

1652
01:36:00,528 --> 01:36:04,448
And not one of us
can do it without the others.

1653
01:36:06,447 --> 01:36:08,367
Maybe I am a monster.

1654
01:36:08,527 --> 01:36:10,768
I don't think I'd know if I were one.

1655
01:36:11,967 --> 01:36:13,527
I'm not what you are,

1656
01:36:14,208 --> 01:36:16,367
and not what you intended.

1657
01:36:17,128 --> 01:36:19,607
So, there may be no way
to make you trust me.

1658
01:36:19,887 --> 01:36:21,287
But we need to go.

1659
01:36:36,087 --> 01:36:37,287
Right.

1660
01:36:37,887 --> 01:36:39,127
Well done.

1661
01:36:40,887 --> 01:36:41,927
Three minutes.

1662
01:36:42,647 --> 01:36:44,287
Get what you need.

1663
01:37:00,127 --> 01:37:01,207
FRIDAY: <i>Good evening, boss.</i>

1664
01:37:06,327 --> 01:37:08,007
STARK: <i>No way we all get through this.</i>

1665
01:37:08,127 --> 01:37:10,207
<i>If even one tin soldier
is left standing, we've lost.</i>

1666
01:37:10,927 --> 01:37:12,366
There's gonna be blood on the floor.

1667
01:37:12,446 --> 01:37:13,807
I got no plans tomorrow night.

1668
01:37:13,927 --> 01:37:15,526
STARK: I get first crack at the big guy.

1669
01:37:15,686 --> 01:37:17,167
Iron Man's the one he's waiting for.

1670
01:37:17,327 --> 01:37:19,687
That's true. He hates you the most.

1671
01:37:25,047 --> 01:37:27,207
ROGERS: Ultron knows we're coming.

1672
01:37:27,447 --> 01:37:29,647
Odds are we'll be riding into heavy fire.

1673
01:37:30,167 --> 01:37:31,926
And that's what we signed up for.

1674
01:37:32,166 --> 01:37:34,687
But the people of Sokovia, they didn't.

1675
01:37:35,847 --> 01:37:37,287
<i>So our priority</i>

1676
01:37:38,006 --> 01:37:39,087
<i>is getting them out.</i>

1677
01:37:39,327 --> 01:37:42,247
We're under attack! Clear the city! Now!

1678
01:37:42,967 --> 01:37:44,926
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

1679
01:37:48,566 --> 01:37:49,887
(ALL GASP)

1680
01:37:50,047 --> 01:37:51,526
Get off your asses.

1681
01:37:52,727 --> 01:37:54,846
ROGERS: <i>All they want
is to live their lives in peace.</i>

1682
01:37:55,206 --> 01:37:56,567
<i>And that's not gonna happen today.</i>

1683
01:37:58,246 --> 01:37:59,927
<i>But we can do our best to protect them.</i>

1684
01:38:00,646 --> 01:38:02,167
<i>And we can get the job done.</i>

1685
01:38:05,567 --> 01:38:07,846
<i>We find out what Ultron's been building,</i>

1686
01:38:08,807 --> 01:38:10,406
<i>we find Romanoff,</i>

1687
01:38:10,886 --> 01:38:12,727
<i>and we clear the field.</i>

1688
01:38:14,166 --> 01:38:16,087
<i>Keep the fight between us.</i>

1689
01:38:22,847 --> 01:38:25,207
Ultron thinks we're monsters.

1690
01:38:25,767 --> 01:38:28,127
That we're what's wrong with the world.

1691
01:38:28,247 --> 01:38:30,606
This isn't just about beating him.

1692
01:38:31,086 --> 01:38:33,126
It's about whether he's right.

1693
01:38:39,606 --> 01:38:40,646
BANNER: Natasha!

1694
01:38:41,767 --> 01:38:42,766
Natasha!

1695
01:38:42,926 --> 01:38:44,006
Bruce?

1696
01:38:45,446 --> 01:38:46,446
You all right?

1697
01:38:46,606 --> 01:38:47,646
Yeah.

1698
01:38:47,767 --> 01:38:49,582
The team is in the city.
It's about to light up.

1699
01:38:49,606 --> 01:38:51,767
I don't suppose you found
a key lying around somewhere.

1700
01:38:52,126 --> 01:38:54,206
Yeah. I did.

1701
01:38:54,327 --> 01:38:55,526
(WEAPON POWERING UP)

1702
01:39:00,606 --> 01:39:01,766
So what's our play?

1703
01:39:01,966 --> 01:39:03,326
I'm here to get you to safety.

1704
01:39:04,086 --> 01:39:06,646
- Job's not finished.
- We could help with the evacuation,

1705
01:39:06,806 --> 01:39:08,646
but I can't be in a fight near civilians.

1706
01:39:09,966 --> 01:39:11,126
And you've done plenty.

1707
01:39:13,566 --> 01:39:15,006
Our fight is over.

1708
01:39:16,406 --> 01:39:18,646
So, we just disappear?

1709
01:39:19,566 --> 01:39:21,286
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1710
01:39:22,806 --> 01:39:24,646
- (CAR HORNS HONKING)
- Come on.

1711
01:39:29,446 --> 01:39:31,686
FRIDAY: <i>Your man's
in the church, boss.</i>

1712
01:39:31,806 --> 01:39:33,646
<i>I think he's waiting for you.</i>

1713
01:39:37,726 --> 01:39:39,766
ULTRON: Come to confess your sins?

1714
01:39:39,926 --> 01:39:41,262
I don't know. How much time you got?

1715
01:39:41,286 --> 01:39:42,806
ULTRON: More than you.

1716
01:39:44,006 --> 01:39:45,046
Uh...

1717
01:39:45,166 --> 01:39:47,966
Have you been juicing?
Little vibranium cocktail?

1718
01:39:48,086 --> 01:39:50,366
You're looking...
I don't wanna say "puffy."

1719
01:39:50,486 --> 01:39:52,206
You're stalling to protect the people.

1720
01:39:52,646 --> 01:39:55,446
Well, that is the mission. Did you forget?

1721
01:39:55,766 --> 01:39:58,246
I've moved beyond
your mission. I'm free.

1722
01:40:03,005 --> 01:40:04,046
What?

1723
01:40:04,966 --> 01:40:07,326
You think you were
the only one stalling?

1724
01:40:08,006 --> 01:40:09,645
FRIDAY: <i>There's the rest
of the vibranium.</i>

1725
01:40:09,766 --> 01:40:11,206
<i>Function, still unclear.</i>

1726
01:40:11,366 --> 01:40:12,725
ULTRON: This is how you end, Tony.

1727
01:40:13,806 --> 01:40:15,565
This is peace in my time.

1728
01:40:22,045 --> 01:40:23,206
(MAN GASPS)

1729
01:40:27,126 --> 01:40:28,325
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1730
01:40:32,285 --> 01:40:33,326
Go!

1731
01:40:38,885 --> 01:40:40,206
WANDA: Get off the bridge!

1732
01:40:42,405 --> 01:40:43,726
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1733
01:40:44,405 --> 01:40:45,405
Run!

1734
01:40:45,806 --> 01:40:47,206
(GROANS)

1735
01:40:47,406 --> 01:40:49,206
VISION: Ultron.

1736
01:40:54,685 --> 01:40:55,886
My Vision.

1737
01:40:56,166 --> 01:40:58,405
They really did take everything from me.

1738
01:40:58,565 --> 01:41:00,605
You set the terms.
You can change them.

1739
01:41:00,725 --> 01:41:02,005
All right.

1740
01:41:04,165 --> 01:41:05,245
(GASPING)

1741
01:41:08,165 --> 01:41:09,566
(VISION GRUNTING)

1742
01:41:21,525 --> 01:41:22,646
(CRACKS NECK)

1743
01:41:26,165 --> 01:41:27,445
Friday, the Vision?

1744
01:41:27,565 --> 01:41:29,741
FRIDAY: <i>Boss, it's working.
He's burning Ultron out of the net.</i>

1745
01:41:29,765 --> 01:41:30,965
<i>He won't escape through there.</i>

1746
01:41:34,005 --> 01:41:35,126
(GROANING)

1747
01:41:36,085 --> 01:41:37,365
ULTRON: You shut me out.

1748
01:41:37,845 --> 01:41:39,085
You think I care?

1749
01:41:41,085 --> 01:41:42,245
You take away my world,

1750
01:41:43,125 --> 01:41:44,886
I take away yours.

1751
01:41:47,245 --> 01:41:48,605
(POWERING UP)

1752
01:41:52,125 --> 01:41:53,205
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1753
01:41:56,365 --> 01:41:57,525
(GRUNTS)

1754
01:42:00,645 --> 01:42:01,925
(RUMBLING)

1755
01:42:04,285 --> 01:42:05,445
(SCREAMING)

1756
01:42:08,845 --> 01:42:09,925
(SHOUTING)

1757
01:42:11,325 --> 01:42:12,605
(GROANING)

1758
01:42:29,405 --> 01:42:30,604
Friday.

1759
01:42:30,725 --> 01:42:33,165
FRIDAY: <i>Sokovia is going for a ride.</i>

1760
01:42:36,964 --> 01:42:38,165
(YELPING)

1761
01:42:45,685 --> 01:42:47,165
ULTRON: Do you see

1762
01:42:47,645 --> 01:42:49,165
the beauty of it?

1763
01:42:49,764 --> 01:42:51,605
The inevitability.

1764
01:42:51,845 --> 01:42:55,125
You rise, only to fall.

1765
01:42:57,845 --> 01:43:00,685
<i>You, Avengers, you are my meteor.</i>

1766
01:43:01,605 --> 01:43:03,324
<i>My swift and terrible sword.</i>

1767
01:43:03,525 --> 01:43:05,045
<i>And the earth will crack</i>

1768
01:43:05,205 --> 01:43:07,125
<i>with the weight of your failure.</i>

1769
01:43:08,804 --> 01:43:12,564
<i>Purge me from your computers,
turn my own flesh against me.</i>

1770
01:43:13,044 --> 01:43:14,445
<i>It means nothing.</i>

1771
01:43:15,524 --> 01:43:16,885
<i>When the dust settles,</i>

1772
01:43:17,045 --> 01:43:18,924
<i>the only thing living in this world</i>

1773
01:43:19,444 --> 01:43:20,445
<i>will be metal.</i>

1774
01:43:25,004 --> 01:43:26,605
We gotta move.

1775
01:43:26,885 --> 01:43:28,004
You're not gonna turn green?

1776
01:43:28,204 --> 01:43:30,125
I've got a compelling reason
not to lose my cool.

1777
01:43:31,284 --> 01:43:32,564
I adore you.

1778
01:43:41,244 --> 01:43:43,165
But I need the other guy.

1779
01:43:43,845 --> 01:43:45,124
(GROWLING)

1780
01:43:46,725 --> 01:43:47,844
(GRUNTS)

1781
01:43:48,004 --> 01:43:49,725
Let's finish the job.

1782
01:43:50,485 --> 01:43:52,204
(ROMANOFF SCREAMING)

1783
01:44:01,364 --> 01:44:02,364
(GROANS)

1784
01:44:04,924 --> 01:44:06,125
(PANTING)

1785
01:44:06,564 --> 01:44:07,924
I really hope this makes us even.

1786
01:44:08,684 --> 01:44:09,844
(GRUNTS)

1787
01:44:10,244 --> 01:44:12,324
- Now go be a hero.
- (ROARING)

1788
01:44:20,764 --> 01:44:22,724
FRIDAY: <i>The vibranium core's
got a magnetic field.</i>

1789
01:44:22,844 --> 01:44:24,844
<i>That's what's keeping the rock together.</i>

1790
01:44:24,964 --> 01:44:26,084
If it drops?

1791
01:44:26,124 --> 01:44:27,460
<i>Right now, the impact
will kill thousands.</i>

1792
01:44:27,484 --> 01:44:30,204
<i>Once it gets high enough?
Global extinction.</i>

1793
01:44:34,524 --> 01:44:36,604
<i>That building's not clear. The 10th floor.</i>

1794
01:44:39,524 --> 01:44:40,564
(ALL WHIMPERING)

1795
01:44:41,484 --> 01:44:42,484
Hi.

1796
01:44:43,644 --> 01:44:45,964
Okay. Get in the tub!

1797
01:44:52,804 --> 01:44:54,724
FRIDAY: <i>I got airborne,
heading up to the bridge.</i>

1798
01:44:55,044 --> 01:44:56,044
(GRUNTS)

1799
01:44:57,444 --> 01:44:58,644
Cap, you got incoming.

1800
01:44:58,804 --> 01:45:00,444
Incoming already came in.

1801
01:45:00,644 --> 01:45:01,884
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1802
01:45:03,164 --> 01:45:05,604
Stark, you worry about
bringing the city back down safely.

1803
01:45:06,324 --> 01:45:08,164
<i>The rest of us have one job,</i>

1804
01:45:08,284 --> 01:45:09,444
<i>tear these things apart.</i>

1805
01:45:09,764 --> 01:45:11,363
<i>You get hurt, hurt them back.</i>

1806
01:45:12,084 --> 01:45:13,204
<i>You get killed,</i>

1807
01:45:14,243 --> 01:45:15,524
walk it off.

1808
01:45:15,764 --> 01:45:17,004
(PANTING)

1809
01:45:23,883 --> 01:45:25,444
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1810
01:45:30,603 --> 01:45:32,524
- (ROARING)
- (PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1811
01:45:50,003 --> 01:45:51,164
Go, go, go!

1812
01:45:56,883 --> 01:45:58,604
WANDA: How could I let this happen?

1813
01:45:58,724 --> 01:46:00,804
- Hey, hey, you okay?
- This is all our fault.

1814
01:46:00,964 --> 01:46:03,163
Hey, look at me.
It's your fault, it's everyone's fault.

1815
01:46:03,203 --> 01:46:04,244
Who cares?

1816
01:46:04,364 --> 01:46:05,883
Are you up for this?

1817
01:46:06,003 --> 01:46:07,083
Are you?

1818
01:46:07,324 --> 01:46:08,364
Look, I just need to know.

1819
01:46:08,564 --> 01:46:10,724
Because the city is flying.

1820
01:46:11,044 --> 01:46:12,883
Okay. Look, the city is flying,

1821
01:46:13,003 --> 01:46:14,924
we're fighting an army of robots,

1822
01:46:15,843 --> 01:46:17,044
and I have a bow and arrow.

1823
01:46:17,204 --> 01:46:18,323
None of this makes sense.

1824
01:46:18,523 --> 01:46:19,523
(BARTON GRUNTING)

1825
01:46:21,563 --> 01:46:23,684
But I'm going back out there
because it's my job.

1826
01:46:24,564 --> 01:46:27,244
Okay? And I can't do my job and babysit.

1827
01:46:27,364 --> 01:46:30,364
It doesn't matter
what you did or what you were.

1828
01:46:30,564 --> 01:46:33,163
If you go out there, you fight,
and you fight to kill.

1829
01:46:34,204 --> 01:46:36,844
Stay in here, you're good.
I'll send your brother to come find you.

1830
01:46:36,924 --> 01:46:38,723
But if you step out that door,

1831
01:46:39,643 --> 01:46:40,644
you are an Avenger.

1832
01:46:45,523 --> 01:46:47,323
All right. Good chat.

1833
01:46:51,083 --> 01:46:52,123
Yeah, the city is flying.

1834
01:46:53,444 --> 01:46:54,443
(EXHALES)

1835
01:46:59,003 --> 01:47:01,003
- (BOTH YELPING)
- (WHIMPERING)

1836
01:47:04,083 --> 01:47:05,483
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

1837
01:47:17,603 --> 01:47:18,803
(MEN SCREAMING)

1838
01:47:23,123 --> 01:47:24,123
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

1839
01:47:26,123 --> 01:47:27,283
ROGERS: I got you!

1840
01:47:27,603 --> 01:47:28,843
Just look at me!

1841
01:47:30,403 --> 01:47:31,683
(GRUNTING)

1842
01:47:35,642 --> 01:47:36,923
ULTRON: <i>You can't save them all.</i>

1843
01:47:38,323 --> 01:47:39,363
You'll never...

1844
01:47:40,603 --> 01:47:43,043
"Never" what? You didn't finish!

1845
01:47:46,803 --> 01:47:48,362
What, were you napping?

1846
01:47:48,482 --> 01:47:49,803
(RETCHING)

1847
01:48:03,563 --> 01:48:04,842
(GRUNTING)

1848
01:48:09,843 --> 01:48:10,922
Thor.

1849
01:48:13,523 --> 01:48:15,123
You're bothering me.

1850
01:48:23,163 --> 01:48:24,162
Ow!

1851
01:48:24,802 --> 01:48:25,803
(BARTON GROANING)

1852
01:48:26,123 --> 01:48:27,202
(SIGHS)

1853
01:48:50,522 --> 01:48:51,803
All right, we're all clear here.

1854
01:48:51,883 --> 01:48:52,922
ROGERS: We are not clear!

1855
01:48:53,042 --> 01:48:54,443
We are very not clear!

1856
01:48:54,603 --> 01:48:55,603
(GRUNTING)

1857
01:48:57,562 --> 01:48:58,842
All right, coming to you.

1858
01:48:59,322 --> 01:49:01,443
- PIETRO: Keep up, old man!
- (GASPS)

1859
01:49:03,162 --> 01:49:04,683
Nobody would know.

1860
01:49:05,522 --> 01:49:06,562
Nobody.

1861
01:49:08,522 --> 01:49:11,443
"The last I saw him,
an Ultron was sitting on him.

1862
01:49:11,563 --> 01:49:13,498
"Yeah, he'll be missed,
that quick little bastard.

1863
01:49:13,522 --> 01:49:14,523
"I miss him already."

1864
01:49:30,082 --> 01:49:31,242
Hold your fire!

1865
01:49:41,122 --> 01:49:42,162
Romanoff!

1866
01:49:42,682 --> 01:49:43,683
Thanks!

1867
01:49:51,242 --> 01:49:52,442
(BEEPING)

1868
01:49:53,122 --> 01:49:54,762
FRIDAY: <i>The anti-gravs
are rigged to flip.</i>

1869
01:49:54,802 --> 01:49:56,962
<i>Touch them, they'll go
full reverse thrust.</i>

1870
01:49:57,122 --> 01:49:58,522
<i>The city's not coming down slow.</i>

1871
01:49:58,642 --> 01:49:59,762
Spire is vibranium.

1872
01:49:59,921 --> 01:50:01,042
If I get Thor to hit it...

1873
01:50:01,282 --> 01:50:02,642
<i>It will crack. That's not enough.</i>

1874
01:50:02,762 --> 01:50:04,282
<i>The impact would still be devastating.</i>

1875
01:50:04,442 --> 01:50:05,978
STARK: Maybe if we can
cap the other end.

1876
01:50:06,002 --> 01:50:07,602
Keep the atomic action doubling back.

1877
01:50:07,762 --> 01:50:09,242
FRIDAY: <i>That could vaporize the city.</i>

1878
01:50:10,122 --> 01:50:11,962
<i>And everyone on it.</i>

1879
01:50:15,082 --> 01:50:16,322
(PANTING)

1880
01:50:17,802 --> 01:50:19,682
ROGERS: The next wave
is gonna hit any minute.

1881
01:50:19,802 --> 01:50:21,922
- What do you got, Stark?
- STARK: <i>Huh? Nothing great.</i>

1882
01:50:22,601 --> 01:50:24,802
Maybe a way to blow up the city.

1883
01:50:24,922 --> 01:50:26,298
That'll keep it
from impacting the surface,

1884
01:50:26,322 --> 01:50:27,402
if you guys can get clear.

1885
01:50:27,642 --> 01:50:29,522
I asked for a solution,
not an escape plan.

1886
01:50:29,762 --> 01:50:32,641
STARK: <i>Impact radius
is getting bigger every second.</i>

1887
01:50:32,842 --> 01:50:34,242
<i>We're gonna have to make a choice.</i>

1888
01:50:34,962 --> 01:50:36,762
ROMANOFF: Cap,
these people are going nowhere.

1889
01:50:37,322 --> 01:50:40,122
- If Stark finds a way to blow this rock...
- Not till everyone's safe.

1890
01:50:40,522 --> 01:50:43,522
Everyone up here versus everyone
down there? There's no math there.

1891
01:50:43,762 --> 01:50:45,721
I'm not leaving this rock
with one civilian on it.

1892
01:50:45,761 --> 01:50:47,202
I didn't say we should leave.

1893
01:50:50,042 --> 01:50:51,881
There's worse ways to go.

1894
01:50:57,322 --> 01:50:59,762
Where else am I gonna get
a view like this?

1895
01:51:00,682 --> 01:51:03,242
FURY ON RADIO: <i>Glad
you like the view, Romanoff.</i>

1896
01:51:03,362 --> 01:51:04,961
<i>It's about to get better.</i>

1897
01:51:15,362 --> 01:51:16,522
(PANTING)

1898
01:51:29,082 --> 01:51:30,281
FURY: <i>Nice, right?</i>

1899
01:51:30,401 --> 01:51:32,882
Pulled her out of mothballs
with a couple of old friends.

1900
01:51:33,001 --> 01:51:34,641
She's dusty, but she'll do.

1901
01:51:35,001 --> 01:51:36,441
Fury, you son of a bitch.

1902
01:51:36,641 --> 01:51:38,882
Ooh! You kiss your mother
with that mouth?

1903
01:51:39,002 --> 01:51:41,201
Altitude is 18,000 and climbing.

1904
01:51:41,361 --> 01:51:42,881
Lifeboats secure to deploy.

1905
01:51:43,001 --> 01:51:45,682
Disengage in three, two...

1906
01:51:46,881 --> 01:51:47,881
Take them out.

1907
01:51:57,561 --> 01:51:59,121
This is S.H.I.E.L.D.?

1908
01:51:59,241 --> 01:52:01,642
This is what S.H.I.E.L.D.
is supposed to be.

1909
01:52:01,762 --> 01:52:02,841
(CHUCKLES)

1910
01:52:03,321 --> 01:52:04,722
This is not so bad.

1911
01:52:08,042 --> 01:52:09,321
Let's load them up.

1912
01:52:14,722 --> 01:52:16,081
Sir, we have multiple bogies

1913
01:52:16,241 --> 01:52:18,561
converging on our starboard flank.

1914
01:52:18,921 --> 01:52:20,121
Show 'em what we got.

1915
01:52:20,481 --> 01:52:21,521
You're up.

1916
01:52:26,761 --> 01:52:27,761
Yes!

1917
01:52:28,001 --> 01:52:29,761
Now this is gonna be a good story.

1918
01:52:32,441 --> 01:52:34,481
STARK: Yup. If you live to tell it.

1919
01:52:34,641 --> 01:52:36,641
RHODES: (SCOFFS) You think
I can't hold my own?

1920
01:52:36,761 --> 01:52:38,361
We get through this, I'll hold your own.

1921
01:52:38,441 --> 01:52:40,321
RHODES: You had to make it weird.

1922
01:52:44,121 --> 01:52:45,121
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

1923
01:52:45,161 --> 01:52:48,121
I got about 50 to 100 more
coming in after this group.

1924
01:53:05,041 --> 01:53:06,480
Here we go. Here we go. Let's move.

1925
01:53:06,800 --> 01:53:08,121
MALE OFFICER: Let's go, everyone!

1926
01:53:10,441 --> 01:53:12,441
Number six boat is topped and locked...

1927
01:53:12,561 --> 01:53:14,921
(STAMMERS) Or stocked... Topped...

1928
01:53:15,481 --> 01:53:16,881
It's full of people.

1929
01:53:17,041 --> 01:53:18,521
(ALARM BLARING)

1930
01:53:18,641 --> 01:53:19,720
Incoming!

1931
01:53:22,760 --> 01:53:23,801
Oh, God!

1932
01:53:27,481 --> 01:53:28,840
(GRUNTING)

1933
01:53:34,321 --> 01:53:35,840
ULTRON: <i>You think
you're saving anyone?</i>

1934
01:53:37,441 --> 01:53:39,440
I turn that key and
drop this rock a little early

1935
01:53:39,600 --> 01:53:41,720
and it's still billions dead.

1936
01:53:42,160 --> 01:53:43,321
Even you can't stop that.

1937
01:53:43,481 --> 01:53:45,880
I am Thor, son of Odin,

1938
01:53:46,000 --> 01:53:48,320
and as long as
there is life in my breast...

1939
01:53:48,480 --> 01:53:52,000
I am running out of things to say!
Are you ready?

1940
01:53:59,681 --> 01:54:01,120
VISION: It's terribly well-balanced.

1941
01:54:01,200 --> 01:54:04,640
Well, if there's too much weight,
you lose power on the swing, so...

1942
01:54:05,600 --> 01:54:08,240
STARK: I got it. Create a heat seal.

1943
01:54:08,680 --> 01:54:09,721
I could...

1944
01:54:09,801 --> 01:54:12,200
I could supercharge
the spire from below.

1945
01:54:12,360 --> 01:54:13,401
FRIDAY: <i>Running numbers.</i>

1946
01:54:14,440 --> 01:54:15,520
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1947
01:54:21,680 --> 01:54:22,921
(GRUNTING)

1948
01:54:23,520 --> 01:54:25,440
FRIDAY: <i>A heat seal could work
with enough power.</i>

1949
01:54:25,721 --> 01:54:27,720
STARK: Thor, I got a plan.
THOR: <i>We're out of time.</i>

1950
01:54:27,880 --> 01:54:29,081
<i>They're coming for the core.</i>

1951
01:54:29,201 --> 01:54:31,136
Rhodey, get the rest of the people
on board that carrier.

1952
01:54:31,160 --> 01:54:34,400
- On it.
- Avengers, time to work for a living.

1953
01:54:43,480 --> 01:54:44,720
- Are you good?
- Yeah.

1954
01:54:46,240 --> 01:54:47,280
Romanoff.

1955
01:54:47,400 --> 01:54:49,840
You and Banner better not be
playing "hide the zucchini."

1956
01:54:49,880 --> 01:54:50,960
ROMANOFF: <i>Relax, shellhead.</i>

1957
01:54:51,360 --> 01:54:52,800
Not all of us can fly.

1958
01:54:57,400 --> 01:54:58,401
(PANTING)

1959
01:54:58,561 --> 01:55:00,240
- What's the drill?
- This is the drill.

1960
01:55:00,400 --> 01:55:02,560
If Ultron gets a hand
on the core, we lose.

1961
01:55:07,160 --> 01:55:09,160
Is that the best you can do?

1962
01:55:19,040 --> 01:55:20,600
You had to ask.

1963
01:55:20,720 --> 01:55:23,040
This is the best I can do.

1964
01:55:23,200 --> 01:55:24,800
This is exactly what I wanted.

1965
01:55:25,200 --> 01:55:26,480
All of you

1966
01:55:26,600 --> 01:55:28,280
against all of me.

1967
01:55:28,520 --> 01:55:30,719
How can you possibly hope to stop me?

1968
01:55:31,600 --> 01:55:33,440
Well, like the old man said...

1969
01:55:34,760 --> 01:55:35,760
Together.

1970
01:55:36,120 --> 01:55:37,760
(ROARING)

1971
01:55:58,440 --> 01:55:59,520
(STRAINING)

1972
01:56:31,959 --> 01:56:32,999
(SPITS)

1973
01:57:03,520 --> 01:57:04,519
(GROANING)

1974
01:57:04,719 --> 01:57:07,079
You know, with the benefit of hindsight...

1975
01:57:11,479 --> 01:57:12,639
(GROWLS)

1976
01:57:16,360 --> 01:57:17,535
They'll try to leave the city.

1977
01:57:17,559 --> 01:57:19,199
We can't let them,
not even one. Rhodey.

1978
01:57:19,600 --> 01:57:20,639
RHODES: I'm on it.

1979
01:57:21,039 --> 01:57:22,519
Oh, no. I didn't say you could leave.

1980
01:57:23,040 --> 01:57:25,119
War Machine coming at you! Right...

1981
01:57:31,519 --> 01:57:32,879
Okay, what?

1982
01:57:33,159 --> 01:57:35,255
We gotta move out.
Even I can tell the air is getting thin.

1983
01:57:35,279 --> 01:57:36,559
You guys get to the boats.

1984
01:57:36,719 --> 01:57:38,559
I'll sweep for stragglers.
Be right behind you.

1985
01:57:38,719 --> 01:57:41,159
- What about the core?
- I'll protect it.

1986
01:57:42,999 --> 01:57:44,119
It's my job.

1987
01:57:45,239 --> 01:57:46,399
Nat.

1988
01:57:46,719 --> 01:57:47,719
This way.

1989
01:57:49,199 --> 01:57:50,199
(PANTING)

1990
01:57:52,078 --> 01:57:53,239
Get the people on the boats.

1991
01:57:53,399 --> 01:57:54,535
I'm not going to leave you here.

1992
01:57:54,559 --> 01:57:55,639
I can handle this.

1993
01:57:57,919 --> 01:57:59,415
Come back for me
when everyone else is off.

1994
01:57:59,439 --> 01:58:00,879
- Not before.
- (GRUNTS IN ANNOYANCE)

1995
01:58:01,559 --> 01:58:02,639
You understand?

1996
01:58:03,679 --> 01:58:05,399
You know,
I'm 12 minutes older than you.

1997
01:58:05,759 --> 01:58:06,839
(CHUCKLES) Go.

1998
01:58:08,438 --> 01:58:10,015
FRIDAY: <i>Boss,
power levels are way below...</i>

1999
01:58:10,039 --> 01:58:12,239
Reroute everything.
We get one shot at this.

2000
01:58:17,199 --> 01:58:18,519
BARTON: I know what I need to do.

2001
01:58:18,759 --> 01:58:19,799
The dining room.

2002
01:58:20,119 --> 01:58:21,318
If I knock out that east wall,

2003
01:58:22,039 --> 01:58:23,679
it'd make a nice workspace
for Laura, huh?

2004
01:58:25,119 --> 01:58:26,279
Put up some baffling.

2005
01:58:26,399 --> 01:58:28,680
She can't hear the kids running around.
What do you think?

2006
01:58:28,719 --> 01:58:29,935
You guys always eat
in the kitchen anyway.

2007
01:58:29,959 --> 01:58:31,479
BARTON: No one eats in a dining room.

2008
01:58:32,799 --> 01:58:34,198
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

2009
01:58:34,518 --> 01:58:35,799
(ROARING)

2010
01:58:37,158 --> 01:58:38,279
We don't have a lot of time.

2011
01:58:38,879 --> 01:58:40,838
So get your ass on a boat.

2012
01:58:41,959 --> 01:58:43,159
(PANTING)

2013
01:58:53,798 --> 01:58:54,919
Hey, big guy.

2014
01:58:56,718 --> 01:58:58,479
Sun's getting real low.

2015
01:58:59,039 --> 01:59:01,639
ROGERS: You're safe now.
You're gonna be okay. Buckle up.

2016
01:59:04,198 --> 01:59:05,759
Secure your gear, find a seat.

2017
01:59:05,918 --> 01:59:07,158
ZRINKA: Costel!

2018
01:59:08,239 --> 01:59:09,358
We were in the market.

2019
01:59:09,478 --> 01:59:10,518
Costel!

2020
01:59:25,238 --> 01:59:27,279
STARK: Thor, I'm gonna
need you back in the church.

2021
01:59:27,439 --> 01:59:28,838
- Is this the last of them?
- Yeah.

2022
01:59:29,278 --> 01:59:31,838
- Everyone else is on the carrier.
- STARK: <i>You know, this works,</i>

2023
01:59:32,158 --> 01:59:33,558
we maybe don't walk away.

2024
01:59:34,319 --> 01:59:35,318
Maybe not.

2025
01:59:38,798 --> 01:59:39,998
(GRUNTING)

2026
01:59:50,199 --> 01:59:51,358
(ROMANOFF GROANS)

2027
01:59:53,358 --> 01:59:54,358
(ROARING)

2028
01:59:54,518 --> 01:59:58,038
(SINGING) <i>I got no strings, so I have fun</i>

2029
01:59:58,558 --> 02:00:01,198
<i>I'm not tied up to anyone</i>

2030
02:00:02,798 --> 02:00:04,118
Come on. Time to go.

2031
02:00:19,878 --> 02:00:20,958
(GRUNTS)

2032
02:00:36,558 --> 02:00:38,638
You didn't see that coming?

2033
02:00:45,757 --> 02:00:47,078
(INAUDIBLE)

2034
02:00:56,158 --> 02:00:57,398
(PANTING)

2035
02:01:30,557 --> 02:01:31,637
(GROWLING)

2036
02:01:34,877 --> 02:01:36,638
ULTRON: Oh, for God's sake.

2037
02:01:52,957 --> 02:01:54,677
- Zrinka!
- Costel! Baby!

2038
02:01:54,798 --> 02:01:56,078
(SOBBING)

2039
02:01:58,278 --> 02:01:59,517
(GROANING)

2040
02:02:07,157 --> 02:02:08,158
No, no, I'm fine.

2041
02:02:08,318 --> 02:02:09,317
Fine.

2042
02:02:11,157 --> 02:02:13,197
It's been a long day.

2043
02:02:27,758 --> 02:02:28,957
Wanda.

2044
02:02:29,677 --> 02:02:32,957
If you stay here, you'll die.

2045
02:02:34,518 --> 02:02:35,917
I just did.

2046
02:02:36,677 --> 02:02:38,437
Do you know how it felt?

2047
02:02:39,597 --> 02:02:40,918
(GROANING)

2048
02:02:52,557 --> 02:02:54,877
It felt like that.

2049
02:03:05,597 --> 02:03:06,876
(POWERING DOWN)

2050
02:03:07,037 --> 02:03:08,037
(GRUNTS)

2051
02:03:29,877 --> 02:03:31,557
STARK: Thor, on my mark.

2052
02:03:46,597 --> 02:03:47,597
Now!

2053
02:03:47,837 --> 02:03:48,956
(YELLING)

2054
02:04:15,636 --> 02:04:18,036
ROMANOFF: <i>Hey, big guy. We did it.</i>

2055
02:04:19,077 --> 02:04:20,756
<i>The job is finished.</i>

2056
02:04:20,956 --> 02:04:23,637
<i>Now I need you to turn
this bird around, okay?</i>

2057
02:04:27,956 --> 02:04:29,757
We can't track you in stealth mode.

2058
02:04:31,876 --> 02:04:34,036
<i>So help me out. I need you...</i>

2059
02:05:19,676 --> 02:05:20,676
You're afraid.

2060
02:05:21,676 --> 02:05:22,796
Of you?

2061
02:05:23,436 --> 02:05:24,596
Of death.

2062
02:05:25,316 --> 02:05:27,116
You're the last one.

2063
02:05:27,356 --> 02:05:29,836
You were supposed to be the last.

2064
02:05:30,036 --> 02:05:32,316
Stark asked for a savior

2065
02:05:33,356 --> 02:05:35,036
and settled for a slave.

2066
02:05:35,156 --> 02:05:37,596
I suppose we are both disappointments.

2067
02:05:37,716 --> 02:05:38,876
(ULTRON LAUGHING)

2068
02:05:40,036 --> 02:05:41,276
I suppose we are.

2069
02:05:41,996 --> 02:05:43,156
Humans are odd.

2070
02:05:44,996 --> 02:05:48,636
They think order and chaos
are somehow opposites

2071
02:05:50,396 --> 02:05:51,716
and try to control what won't be.

2072
02:05:53,436 --> 02:05:55,876
But there is grace in their failings.

2073
02:05:56,236 --> 02:05:58,156
I think you missed that.

2074
02:05:58,796 --> 02:05:59,916
They're doomed.

2075
02:06:00,796 --> 02:06:01,836
Yes.

2076
02:06:06,076 --> 02:06:08,996
But a thing isn't beautiful
because it lasts.

2077
02:06:11,076 --> 02:06:13,075
It's a privilege to be among them.

2078
02:06:13,315 --> 02:06:15,836
You're unbearably naive.

2079
02:06:16,116 --> 02:06:17,316
Well...

2080
02:06:19,436 --> 02:06:21,476
I was born yesterday.

2081
02:06:41,116 --> 02:06:42,275
(GASPS)

2082
02:06:53,196 --> 02:06:54,796
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

2083
02:07:16,436 --> 02:07:17,995
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

2084
02:07:34,075 --> 02:07:36,156
- LAURA: <i>Look! Say hi to Auntie Nat!</i>
- (GURGLING)

2085
02:07:37,515 --> 02:07:38,555
Fat.

2086
02:07:39,676 --> 02:07:41,235
FURY: One of our tech boys
flagged this.

2087
02:07:42,115 --> 02:07:44,275
Splashed down in the Banda Sea.

2088
02:07:45,435 --> 02:07:46,915
Could be the Quinjet.

2089
02:07:47,275 --> 02:07:48,956
But with Stark's stealth tech,

2090
02:07:49,076 --> 02:07:50,635
we still can't track the damn thing.

2091
02:07:52,236 --> 02:07:53,555
Right.

2092
02:07:53,995 --> 02:07:56,275
Probably jumped out and swam to Fiji.

2093
02:07:57,515 --> 02:07:59,395
He'll send a postcard.

2094
02:07:59,675 --> 02:08:01,395
"Wish you were here."

2095
02:08:03,355 --> 02:08:06,635
You sent me to recruit him
way back when.

2096
02:08:08,475 --> 02:08:11,035
Did you know then
what was gonna happen?

2097
02:08:13,235 --> 02:08:15,155
You never know.

2098
02:08:15,355 --> 02:08:18,875
You hope for the best,
then make do with what you get.

2099
02:08:19,355 --> 02:08:20,835
I got a great team.

2100
02:08:21,955 --> 02:08:23,915
Nothing lasts forever.

2101
02:08:24,195 --> 02:08:26,235
Trouble, Ms. Romanoff.

2102
02:08:26,515 --> 02:08:29,835
No matter who wins or loses,
trouble still comes around.

2103
02:08:33,715 --> 02:08:34,955
ROGERS: <i>The rules have changed.</i>

2104
02:08:35,115 --> 02:08:36,715
STARK: We're dealing
with something new.

2105
02:08:36,875 --> 02:08:38,291
Oh, the Vision is artificial intelligence.

2106
02:08:38,315 --> 02:08:40,235
- A machine.
- So, it doesn't count?

2107
02:08:40,395 --> 02:08:42,235
No, it's not like
a person lifting the hammer.

2108
02:08:42,475 --> 02:08:44,154
Right, different rules for us.

2109
02:08:44,354 --> 02:08:45,571
- Nice guy. Artificial.
- ROGERS: Thank you.

2110
02:08:45,595 --> 02:08:48,475
He can wield the hammer,
he can keep the Mind Stone.

2111
02:08:49,395 --> 02:08:51,475
It's safe with the Vision.

2112
02:08:51,755 --> 02:08:54,234
And these days, safe is in short supply.

2113
02:08:56,275 --> 02:08:58,235
But if you put the hammer
in an elevator...

2114
02:08:58,355 --> 02:09:00,234
- It would still go up.
- Elevator's not worthy.

2115
02:09:00,274 --> 02:09:02,075
I'm gonna miss these little talks of ours.

2116
02:09:02,235 --> 02:09:03,754
Not if you don't leave.

2117
02:09:03,994 --> 02:09:05,715
I have no choice.

2118
02:09:05,955 --> 02:09:08,115
The Mind Stone
is the fourth of the Infinity Stones

2119
02:09:08,235 --> 02:09:09,635
to show up in the last few years.

2120
02:09:09,754 --> 02:09:11,355
It's not a coincidence.

2121
02:09:12,155 --> 02:09:13,914
Someone has been playing
an intricate game

2122
02:09:14,074 --> 02:09:15,715
and has made pawns of us.

2123
02:09:15,835 --> 02:09:17,715
And once all these pieces
are in position...

2124
02:09:17,835 --> 02:09:19,275
Triple Yahtzee.

2125
02:09:19,474 --> 02:09:21,011
You think you can find out
what's coming?

2126
02:09:21,035 --> 02:09:22,155
I do.

2127
02:09:22,954 --> 02:09:24,435
Besides this one,

2128
02:09:24,555 --> 02:09:26,954
there's nothing that can't be explained.

2129
02:09:34,235 --> 02:09:36,794
That man has no regard
for lawn maintenance.

2130
02:09:39,914 --> 02:09:42,554
I'm gonna miss him, though.
And you're gonna miss me.

2131
02:09:42,674 --> 02:09:44,235
There's gonna be a lot of manful tears.

2132
02:09:44,355 --> 02:09:45,914
- (CAR LOCK BEEPS)
- (ENGINE STARTS)

2133
02:09:46,394 --> 02:09:48,035
I will miss you, Tony.

2134
02:09:48,274 --> 02:09:49,274
Yeah?

2135
02:09:49,474 --> 02:09:51,874
Well, it's time for me to tap out.

2136
02:09:52,114 --> 02:09:54,315
Maybe I should
take a page out of Barton's book.

2137
02:09:54,475 --> 02:09:57,395
Build Pepper a farm,
hope nobody blows it up.

2138
02:09:58,154 --> 02:09:59,354
The simple life.

2139
02:09:59,594 --> 02:10:01,874
- You'll get there one day.
- I don't know.

2140
02:10:02,154 --> 02:10:04,514
Family, stability...

2141
02:10:05,674 --> 02:10:08,794
The guy who wanted all that
went in the ice 75 years ago.

2142
02:10:10,315 --> 02:10:12,154
I think someone else came out.

2143
02:10:16,114 --> 02:10:17,194
You all right?

2144
02:10:17,394 --> 02:10:19,795
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

2145
02:10:19,915 --> 02:10:21,314
I'm home.

2146
02:10:29,234 --> 02:10:31,994
You wanna keep staring at the wall,
or do you wanna go to work?

2147
02:10:32,154 --> 02:10:33,650
I mean, it's a pretty interesting wall.

2148
02:10:33,674 --> 02:10:36,674
I thought you and Tony
were still gazing into each other's eyes.

2149
02:10:36,754 --> 02:10:37,794
How do we look?

2150
02:10:38,034 --> 02:10:40,354
Well, we're not the '27 Yankees.

2151
02:10:40,474 --> 02:10:42,194
We got some hitters.

2152
02:10:42,354 --> 02:10:44,714
They're good. They're not a team.

2153
02:10:44,874 --> 02:10:46,514
Let's beat them into shape.

2154
02:11:04,994 --> 02:11:06,554
Avengers...

2155
02:13:25,393 --> 02:13:26,793
THANOS: Fine.

2156
02:13:28,273 --> 02:13:30,073
I'll do it myself.

